column7: to go through, go about, to spread
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G2064) erchomai; to traverse (literally) -- come, depart, go (about, abroad, everywhere, over, through, throughout), pass (by, over, through, throughout), pierce through, travel, walk through. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2064) erchomai

column8: to ask about, learn by inquiry
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G2065) erotao; to question throughout, i.e. Ascertain by interrogation -- make enquiry foreign see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2065) erotao

column7: lasting two years, two years old
column9: From  (G1364) dis and  (G2094) etos; of two years (in age) -- two years old. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G2094) etos
From  (G1332) dietes; a space of two years (biennium) -- two years. see GREEK  (G1332) dietes
From  (G1223) dia and  (G2233) hegeomai; to relate fully -- declare, shew, tell. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2233) hegeomai
From  (G1334) diegeomai; a recital -- declaration. see GREEK  (G1334) diegeomai

Neuter of a compound of  (G1223) dia and a derivative of an alternate of  (G5342) phero; carried through, i.e. (adverbially with  (G1519) eis and  (G3588) ho prefixed) perpetually -- + continually, for ever. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5342) phero see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G3588) ho

column7: divided into two seas, dividing the sea (as a reef)
column9: From  (G1364) dis and  (G2281) thalassa; having two seas, i.e. A sound with a double outlet -- where two seas meet. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G2281) thalassa
From  (G1223) dia and the base of  (G2425) hikanos; to reach through, i.e. Penetrate -- pierce. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2425) hikanos

column7: to set apart, to intervene, make an interval
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G2476) histemi; to stand apart, i.e. (reflexively) to remove, intervene -- go further, be parted, after the space of. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2476) histemi
From  (G1223) dia and a derivative of  (G2478) ischuros; to stout it through, i.e. Asservate -- confidently (constantly) affirm. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2478) ischuros
From  (G1342) dikaios and  (G2920) krisis; a just sentence -- righteous judgment. see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios see GREEK  (G2920) krisis
From  (G1349) dike; equitable (in character or act); by implication, innocent, holy (absolutely or relatively) -- just, meet, right(-eous). see GREEK  (G1349) dike
From  (G1342) dikaios; equity (of character or act); specially (Christian) justification -- righteousness. see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios

column7: to show to be righteous, declare righteous
column9: From  (G1342) dikaios; to render (i.e. Show or regard as) just or innocent -- free, justify(-ier), be righteous. see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios

column7: an ordinance, a sentence of acquittal or condemnation, a righteous deed
column9: From  (G1344) dikaioo; an equitable deed; by implication, a statute or decision -- judgment, justification, ordinance, righteousness. see GREEK  (G1344) dikaioo
Adverb from  (G1342) dikaios; equitably -- justly, (to) righteously(-ness). see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios

column7: the act of pronouncing righteous, acquittal
column9: From  (G1344) dikaioo; aquittal (for Christ's sake) -- justification. see GREEK  (G1344) dikaioo
From a derivative of  (G1349) dike; a judger -- judge. see GREEK  (G1349) dike

column7: right (as self-evident), justice (the principle, a decision or its execution)
column9: Probably from  (G1166) deiknuo; right (as self-evident), i.e. Justice (the principle, a decision, or its execution) -- judgment, punish, vengeance. see GREEK  (G1166) deiknuo
Probably from a primary verb diko (to cast); a seine (for fishing) -- net.
From  (G1364) dis and  (G3056) logos; equivocal, i.e. Telling a different story -- double-tongued. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G3056) logos
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3739) hos; through which thing, i.e. Consequently -- for which cause, therefore, wherefore. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3739) hos
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3593) hodeuo; to travel through -- go throughout, pass through. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3593) hodeuo
From Dionusos (Bacchus); reveller; Dionysius, an Athenian -- Dionysius.
From  (G1352) dio and  (G4007) per; on which very account -- wherefore. see GREEK  (G1352) dio see GREEK  (G4007) per
From the alternate of  (G2203) Zeus and the alternate of  (G4098) pipto; sky-fallen (i.e. An aerolite) -- which fell down from Jupiter. see GREEK  (G2203) Zeus see GREEK  (G4098) pipto

From a compound of  (G1223) dia and a derivative of  (G3717) orthos, meaning to straighten thoroughly; rectification, i.e. (specially) the Messianic restauration -- reformation. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3717) orthos

column7: to dig through (as of breaking into a house)
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G3736) orusso; to penetrate burglariously -- break through (up). see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3736) orusso

column7: the Dioscuri, twin sons of Zeus (Castor and Pollux)
column9: From the alternate of  (G2203) Zeus and a form of the base of  (G2877) korasion; sons of Jupiter, i.e. The twins Dioscuri -- Castor and Pollux. see GREEK  (G2203) Zeus see GREEK  (G2877) korasion

column7: on the very account that, because, inasmuch as
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G3754) hoti; on the very account that, or inasmuch as -- because (that), for, therefore. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3754) hoti

column7: cherished by Zeus, Diotrephes, an opponent of the apostle John
column9: From the alternate of  (G2203) Zeus and  (G5142) trepho; Jove-nourished; Diotrephes, an opponent of Christianity -- Diotrephes. see GREEK  (G2203) Zeus see GREEK  (G5142) trepho
From  (G1364) dis and (probably) the base of  (G4119) pleion; two-fold -- double, two-fold more. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G4119) pleion
From  (G1362) diplous; to render two-fold -- double. see GREEK  (G1362) diplous
Adverb from  (G1417) duo; twice -- again, twice. see GREEK  (G1417) duo
From  (G1364) dis; properly, to duplicate, i.e. (mentally) to waver (in opinion) -- doubt. see GREEK  (G1364) dis
From  (G1364) dis and  (G4750) stoma; double-edged -- with two edges, two-edged. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G4750) stoma
From  (G1364) dis and  (G5507) chilioi; two thousand -- two thousand. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G5507) chilioi
From  (G1223) dia and hulizo hoo-lid'-zo (to filter); to strain out -- strain at (probably by misprint). see GREEK  (G1223) dia

column7: to cause a separation, separate, alienate
column9: From a derivative of  (G1364) dis; to make apart, i.e. Sunder (figuratively, alienate) -- set at variance. see GREEK  (G1364) dis
From a derivative of  (G1364) dis and  (G4714) stasis; disunion, i.e. (figuratively) dissension -- division, sedition. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G4714) stasis

column7: to cut in two, cut asunder
column9: From a compound of a derivative of  (G1364) dis and a derivative of temno (to cut); to bisect, i.e. (by extension) to flog severely -- cut asunder (in sunder). see GREEK  (G1364) dis
From a variation of  (G1373) dipsos; to thirst for (literally or figuratively) -- (be, be a-)thirst(-y). see GREEK  (G1373) dipsos
Of uncertain affinity; thirst -- thirst.
From  (G1364) dis and  (G5590) psuche; two-spirited, i.e. Vacillating (in opinion or purpose) -- double minded. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G5590) psuche
From  (G1377) dioko; persecution -- persecution. see GREEK  (G1377) dioko
From  (G1377) dioko; a persecutor -- persecutor. see GREEK  (G1377) dioko

column7: to put to flight, pursue, by implication to persecute
column8: ensue, follow after, persecute, suffer persecution.
column9: A prolonged (and causative) form of a primary verb dio (to flee; compare the base of  (G1169) deilos and  (G1249) diakonos); to pursue (literally or figuratively); by implication, to persecute -- ensue, follow (after), given to, (suffer) persecute(-ion), press forward. see GREEK  (G1169) deilos see GREEK  (G1249) diakonos
From the base of  (G1380) dokeo; a law (civil, ceremonial or ecclesiastical) -- decree, ordinance. see GREEK  (G1380) dokeo

column7: to decree, to subject oneself to an ordinance
column9: From  (G1378) dogma; to prescribe by statute, i.e. (reflexively) to submit to, ceremonially rule -- be subject to ordinances. see GREEK  (G1378) dogma

column7: to have an opinion, to seem
column8: be of reputation, seem good, suppose, think.
column9: A prolonged form of a primary verb, doko dok'-o (used only in an alternate in certain tenses; compare the base of  (G1166) deiknuo) of the same meaning; to think; by implication, to seem (truthfully or uncertainly) -- be accounted, (of own) please(-ure), be of reputation, seem (good), suppose, think, trow. see GREEK  (G1166) deiknuo

column7: to test, by implication to approve
column9: From  (G1384) dokimos; to test (literally or figuratively); by implication, to approve -- allow, discern, examine, X like, (ap-)prove, try. see GREEK  (G1384) dokimos

column7: (the process or result of) trial, proving, approval
column9: From the same as  (G1384) dokimos; test (abstractly or concretely); by implication, trustiness -- experience(-riment), proof, trial. see GREEK  (G1384) dokimos
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G1382) dokime; a testing; by implication, trustworthiness -- trial, trying. see GREEK  (G1382) dokime
From  (G1380) dokeo; properly, acceptable (current after assayal), i.e. Approved -- approved, tried. see GREEK  (G1380) dokeo
From  (G1209) dechomai (through the idea of holding up); a stick of timber -- beam. see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From  (G1388) dolos; guileful -- deceitful. see GREEK  (G1388) dolos
From  (G1386) dolios; to be guileful -- use deceit. see GREEK  (G1386) dolios
From an obsolete primary verb, dello (probably meaning to decoy; compare  (G1185) deleazo); a trick (bait), i.e. (figuratively) wile -- craft, deceit, guile, subtilty. see GREEK  (G1185) deleazo
From  (G1388) dolos; to ensnare, i.e. (figuratively) adulterate -- handle deceitfully. see GREEK  (G1388) dolos
From the base of  (G1325) didomi; a present -- gift. see GREEK  (G1325) didomi

column7: opinion (always good in NT), praise, honor, glory
column9: From the base of  (G1380) dokeo; glory (as very apparent), in a wide application (literal or figurative, objective or subjective) -- dignity, glory(-ious), honour, praise, worship. see GREEK  (G1380) dokeo

column7: to render or esteem glorious (in a wide application)
column9: From  (G1391) doxa; to render (or esteem) glorious (in a wide application) -- (make) glorify(-ious), full of (have) glory, honour, magnify. see GREEK  (G1391) doxa

column7: gazelle (an animal with large bright eyes), Dorcas, a Christian woman
column9: Gazelle; Dorcas, a Christian woman -- Dorcas.

column7: the act of giving, a gift
column9: From the base of  (G1325) didomi; a giving; by implication, (concretely) a gift -- gift, giving. see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From the base of  (G1325) didomi; a giver -- giver. see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From a presumed compound of  (G1401) doulos and  (G71) ago; to be a slave-driver, i.e. To enslave (figuratively, subdue) -- bring into subjection. see GREEK  (G1401) doulos see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G1398) douleuo; slavery (ceremonially or figuratively) -- bondage. see GREEK  (G1398) douleuo

column7: to be a slave, to serve
column9: From  (G1401) doulos; to be a slave to (literal or figurative, involuntary or voluntary) -- be in bondage, (do) serve(-ice). see GREEK  (G1401) doulos
Feminine of  (G1401) doulos; a female slave (involuntarily or voluntarily) -- handmaid(-en). see GREEK  (G1401) doulos
Neuter of  (G1401) doulos; subservient -- servant. see GREEK  (G1401) doulos
From  (G1210) deo; a slave (literal or figurative, involuntary or voluntary; frequently, therefore in a qualified sense of subjection or subserviency) -- bond(-man), servant. see GREEK  (G1210) deo

column8: bring into bondage, become a servant.
column9: From  (G1401) doulos; to enslave (literally or figuratively) -- bring into (be under) bondage, X given, become (make) servant. see GREEK  (G1401) doulos
From  (G1209) dechomai; a reception, i.e. Convivial entertainment -- feast. see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
Probably from an alternate form of derkomai (to look); a fabulous kind of serpent (perhaps as supposed to fascinate) -- dragon.
Perhaps akin to the base of  (G1404) drakon (through the idea of capturing); to grasp, i.e. (figuratively) entrap -- take. see GREEK  (G1404) drakon

column7: as much as one can hold in the hand, a drachma (a Greek  coin made of silver)
column9: From  (G1405) drassomai; a drachma or (silver) coin (as handled) -- piece (of silver). see GREEK  (G1405) drassomai
From drepo (to pluck); a gathering hook (especially for harvesting) -- sickle.
From the alternate of  (G5143) trecho; a race, i.e. (figuratively) career -- course. see GREEK  (G5143) trecho

column7: Drusilla, a member of the Herodian family
column9: A feminine diminutive of Drusus (a Roman name); Drusilla, a member of the Herodian family -- Drusilla.

column7: to be able, to have power
column9: Of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible -- be able, can (do, + -not), could, may, might, be possible, be of power.

From  (G1410) dunamai; force (literally or figuratively); specially, miraculous power (usually by implication, a miracle itself) -- ability, abundance, meaning, might(-ily, -y, -y deed), (worker of) miracle(-s), power, strength, violence, mighty (wonderful) work. see GREEK  (G1410) dunamai
From  (G1411) dunamis; to enable -- strengthen. see GREEK  (G1411) dunamis
From  (G1410) dunamai; a ruler or officer -- of great authority, mighty, potentate. see GREEK  (G1410) dunamai
From  (G1415) dunatos; to be efficient (figuratively) -- be mighty. see GREEK  (G1415) dunatos
From  (G1410) dunamai; powerful or capable (literally or figuratively); neuter possible -- able, could, (that is) mighty (man), possible, power, strong. see GREEK  (G1410) dunamai
Or dumi doo'-mee prolonged forms of an obsolete primary duo doo'-o (to sink) to go "down" -- set.
A primary numeral; "two" -- both, twain, two.

column7: like un- or mis- (as in unrest, misjudge), nullifies good sense or increases bad sense of a word
column9: A primary inseparable particle of uncertain derivation; used only in composition as a prefix; hard, i.e. With difficulty -- + hard, + grievous, etc.
From  (G1418) dus- and a derivative of  (G941) bastazo; oppressive -- grievous to be borne. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G941) bastazo
From  (G1418) dus- and a comparative of  (G1787) entos (meaning a bowel); a "dysentery" -- bloody flux. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G1787) entos
From  (G1418) dus- and a presumed derivative of  (G2059) hermeneuo; difficult of explanation -- hard to be uttered. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G2059) hermeneuo
From  (G1418) dus- and kolon (food); properly, fastidious about eating (peevish), i.e. (genitive case) impracticable -- hard. see GREEK  (G1418) dus-
Adverb from  (G1422) duskolos; impracticably -- hardly. see GREEK  (G1422) duskolos

column7: a setting (as of the sun), by implication (the) western (region)
column9: From  (G1416) duno; the sun-set, i.e. (by implication) the western region -- west. see GREEK  (G1416) duno
From  (G1418) dus- and a derivative of  (G3539) noieo; difficult of perception -- hard to be understood. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G3539) noieo

column7: to use evil words, to speak ill of
column9: From a compound of  (G1418) dus- and  (G5345) pheme; defamation -- evil report. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G5345) pheme
From  (G1417) duo and  (G1176) deka; two and ten, i.e. A dozen -- twelve. see GREEK  (G1417) duo see GREEK  (G1176) deka
From  (G1427) dodeka; twelfth -- twelfth. see GREEK  (G1427) dodeka
From  (G1427) dodeka and  (G5443) phule; the commonwealth of Israel -- twelve tribes. see GREEK  (G1427) dodeka see GREEK  (G5443) phule
From demo (to build); properly, an edifice, i.e. (specially) a roof -- housetop.
From  (G1435) doron; a gratuity -- gift. see GREEK  (G1435) doron

column7: as a gift, to no purpose
column8: without a cause, freely, for naught, in vain.
column9: Accusative case of  (G1431) dorea as adverb; gratuitously (literally or figuratively) -- without a cause, freely, for naught, in vain. see GREEK  (G1431) dorea
Middle voice from  (G1435) doron; to bestow gratuitously -- give. see GREEK  (G1435) doron
From  (G1433) doreomai; a bestowment -- gift. see GREEK  (G1433) doreomai
A present; specially, a sacrifice -- gift, offering.

column7: ah! ha! (interjection expressing surprise, indignation, fear)
column9: Apparent imperative of  (G1439) eao; properly, let it be, i.e. (as interjection) aha! -- let alone. see GREEK  (G1439) eao

From  (G1487) ei and  (G302) an; a conditional particle; in case that, provided, etc.; often used in connection with other particles to denote indefiniteness or uncertainty -- before, but, except, (and) if, (if) so, (what-, whither-)soever, though, when (-soever), whether (or), to whom, (who-)so(-ever). See  (G3361) me. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G302) an see GREEK  (G3361) me

From a reflexive pronoun otherwise obsolete and the genitive case (dative case or accusative case) of  (G846) autos; him- (her-, it-, them-, also (in conjunction with the personal pronoun of the other persons) my-, thy-, our-, your-) self (selves), etc. -- alone, her (own, -self), (he) himself, his (own), itself, one (to) another, our (thine) own(-selves), + that she had, their (own, own selves), (of) them(-selves), they, thyself, you, your (own, own conceits, own selves, -selves). see GREEK  (G846) autos
Of uncertain affinity; to let be, i.e. Permit or leave alone -- commit, leave, let (alone), suffer. See also  (G1436) ea. see GREEK  (G1436) ea
From  (G1442) hebdomos and a modified form of  (G1176) deka; seventy -- seventy, three score and ten. see GREEK  (G1442) hebdomos see GREEK  (G1176) deka
Multiple adverb from  (G1440) hebdomekonta; seventy times -- seventy times. see GREEK  (G1440) hebdomekonta
Ordinal from  (G2033) hepta; seventh -- seventh. see GREEK  (G2033) hepta
Of Hebrew origin ( (H5677) Eber); Eber, a patriarch -- Eber. see HEBREW  (H5677) Eber
From  (G1443) Eber; Hebraic or the Jewish language -- Hebrew. see GREEK  (G1443) Eber
From  (G1443) Eber; a Hebr?An (i.e. Hebrew) or Jew -- Hebrew. see GREEK  (G1443) Eber

column7: Hebrew, the Aramaic vernacular of Pal
column9: From  (G1443) Eber; the Hebraistic (Hebrew) or Jewish (Chaldee) language -- Hebrew. see GREEK  (G1443) Eber
Adverb from  (G1446) Hebrais; Hebraistically or in the Jewish (Chaldee) language -- in (the) Hebrew (tongue). see GREEK  (G1446) Hebrais

column7: to make near, to come near
column8: approach, be at hand, draw near.
column9: From  (G1451) eggus; to make near, i.e. (reflexively) approach -- approach, be at hand, come (draw) near, be (come, draw) nigh. see GREEK  (G1451) eggus

column7: to inscribe, to enter in a register
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G1125) grapho; to "engrave", i.e. Inscribe -- write (in). see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G1125) grapho
From  (G1722) en and guion (a limb); pledged (as if articulated by a member), i.e. A bondsman -- surety. see GREEK  (G1722) en

From a primary verb agcho (to squeeze or throttle; akin to the base of  (G43) agkale); near (literally or figuratively, of place or time) -- from, at hand, near, nigh (at hand, unto), ready. see GREEK  (G43) agkale
Neuter of the comparative of  (G1451) eggus; nearer -- nearer. see GREEK  (G1451) eggus

Probably akin to the base of  (G58) agora (through the idea of collecting one's faculties); to waken (transitively or intransitively), i.e. Rouse (literally, from sleep, from sitting or lying, from disease, from death; or figuratively, from obscurity, inactivity, ruins, nonexistence) -- awake, lift (up), raise (again, up), rear up, (a-)rise (again, up), stand, take up. see GREEK  (G58) agora
From  (G1453) egeiro; a resurgence (from death) -- resurrection. see GREEK  (G1453) egeiro

column7: hired to lie in wait, lying in wait
column9: From  (G1722) en and a derivative of  (G2524) kathiemi; subinduced, i.e. Surreptitiously suborned as a lier-in-wait -- spy. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2524) kathiemi

Neuter plural of a presumed compound from  (G1722) en and  (G2537) kainos; innovatives, i.e. (specially) renewal (of religious services after the Antiochian interruption) -- dedication. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2537) kainos
From  (G1456) egkainia; to renew, i.e. Inaugurate -- consecrate, dedicate. see GREEK  (G1456) egkainia

column7: to call in (as a debt or demand), bring to account
column8: accuse, call in question, lay to the charge.
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2564) kaleo; to call in (as a debt or demand), i.e. Bring to account (charge, criminate, etc.) -- accuse, call in question, implead, lay to the charge. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2564) kaleo

column7: to leave behind, (in a good sense) let remain over or (in a bad sense) desert
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2641) kataleipo; to leave behind in some place, i.e. (in a good sense) let remain over, or (in a bad sense) to desert -- forsake, leave. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2641) kataleipo

column7: to settle down in (a place), reside
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2730) katoikeo; to settle down in a place, i.e. Reside -- dwell among. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2730) katoikeo

column7: to take pride in, glory in
column9: From  (G1722) en and a derivative of  (G2759) kentron; to prick in, i.e. Ingraft -- graff in(-to). see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2759) kentron
From  (G1458) egkaleo; an accusation, i.e. Offence alleged -- crime laid against, laid to charge. see GREEK  (G1458) egkaleo

column7: to put on oneself (as a garment)
column9: Middle voice from  (G1722) en and komboo (to gird); to engirdle oneself (for labor), i.e. Figuratively (the apron as being a badge of servitude) to wear (in token of mutual deference) -- be clothed with. see GREEK  (G1722) en
From  (G1465) egkopto; a hindrance -- X hinder. see GREEK  (G1465) egkopto
From  (G1722) en and  (G2875) kopto; to cut into, i.e. (figuratively) impede, detain -- hinder, be tedious unto. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2875) kopto
From  (G1468) egkrates; self-control (especially continence) -- temperance. see GREEK  (G1468) egkrates
Middle voice from  (G1468) egkrates; to exercise self-restraint (in diet and chastity) -- can(-not) contain, be temperate. see GREEK  (G1468) egkrates

From  (G1722) en and  (G2904) kratos; strong in a thing (masterful), i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) self-controlled (in appetite, etc.) -- temperate. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2904) kratos

column7: to judge in, to reckon among
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2919) krino; to judge in, i.e. Count among -- make of the number. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2919) krino
From  (G1722) en and  (G2928) krupto; to conceal in, i.e. Incorporate with -- hid in. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2928) krupto
From  (G1722) en and the base of  (G2949) kuma; swelling inside, i.e. Pregnant -- great with child. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2949) kuma
From  (G1722) en and  (G5548) chrio; to rub in (oil), i.e. Besmear -- anoint. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G5548) chrio

A primary pronoun of the first person I (only expressed when emphatic) -- I, me. For the other cases and the plural see  (G1691) eme,  (G1698) emoi,  (G1700) emou,  (G2248) hemas,  (G2249) hemeis,  (G2254) hemin,  (G2257) hemon, etc. see GREEK  (G1691) eme see GREEK  (G1698) emoi see GREEK  (G1700) emou see GREEK  (G2248) hemas see GREEK  (G2249) hemeis see GREEK  (G2254) hemin see GREEK  (G2257) hemon

column8: lay even with the ground, raze
column9: From  (G1475) edaphos; to raze -- lay even with the ground. see GREEK  (G1475) edaphos
From the base of  (G1476) hedraios; a basis (bottom), i.e. The soil -- ground. see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios
From a derivative of hezomai (to sit); sedentary, i.e. (by implication) immovable -- settled, stedfast.
From a derivative of  (G1476) hedraios; a support, i.e. (figuratively) basis -- ground. see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios
Of Hebrew origin ( (H2396) Chizqiyah); Ezekias (i.e. Hezekeiah), an Israelite -- Ezekias. see HEBREW  (H2396) Chizqiyah
From  (G2309) ethelo and  (G2356) threskeia; voluntary (arbitrary and unwarranted) piety, i.e. Sanctimony -- will worship. see GREEK  (G2309) ethelo see GREEK  (G2356) threskeia
From  (G1485) ethos; to accustom, i.e. (neuter passive participle) customary -- custom. see GREEK  (G1485) ethos

column7: an ethnarch, a governor (not king) of a province
column9: From  (G1484) ethnos and  (G746) arche; the governor (not king) of a district -- ethnarch. see GREEK  (G1484) ethnos see GREEK  (G746) arche
From  (G1484) ethnos; national ("ethnic"), i.e. (specially) a Gentile -- heathen (man). see GREEK  (G1484) ethnos
Adverb from  (G1482) ethnikos; as a Gentile -- after the manner of Gentiles. see GREEK  (G1482) ethnikos

column7: a race, a nation, the nations (as distinct from Israel)
column9: Probably from  (G1486) etho; a race (as of the same habit), i.e. A tribe; specially, a foreign (non-Jewish) one (usually, by implication, pagan) -- Gentile, heathen, nation, people. see GREEK  (G1486) etho

column7: custom, a usage (prescribed by habit or law)
column9: From  (G1486) etho; a usage (prescribed by habit or law) -- custom, manner, be wont. see GREEK  (G1486) etho
A primary verb; to be used (by habit or conventionality); neuter perfect participle usage -- be custom (manner, wont).

A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc. -- forasmuch as, if, that, (al-)though, whether. Often used in connection or composition with other particles, especially as in  (G1489) eige,  (G1490) ei de me(ge),  (G1499) ei kai,  (G1508) ei me,  (G1509) ei me ti,  (G1512) ei per,  (G1513) ei pos,  (G1536) ei tis,  (G1537) ek. See also  (G1437) ean. see GREEK  (G1489) eige see GREEK  (G1490) ei de me(ge) see GREEK  (G1499) ei kai see GREEK  (G1508) ei me see GREEK  (G1509) ei me ti see GREEK  (G1512) ei per see GREEK  (G1513) ei pos
Second person singular present of  (G1510) eimi; thou art -- art, be. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column7: if indeed, seeing that, unless, with negative otherwise
column9: From  (G1487) ei and  (G1065) ge; if indeed, seeing that, unless, (with negative) otherwise -- if (so be that, yet). see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G1065) ge

From  (G1487) ei,  (G1161) de, and  (G3361) me (sometimes with  (G1065) ge added); but if not -- (or) else, if (not, otherwise), otherwise. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G1161) de see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G1065) ge
From  (G1492) eido; a view, i.e. Form (literally or figuratively) -- appearance, fashion, shape, sight. see GREEK  (G1492) eido

A primary verb; used only in certain past tenses, the others being borrowed from the equivalent  (G3700) optanomai and  (G3708) horao; properly, to see (literally or figuratively); by implication, (in the perfect tense only) to know -- be aware, behold, X can (+ not tell), consider, (have) know(-ledge), look (on), perceive, see, be sure, tell, understand, wish, wot. Compare  (G3700) optanomai. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai see GREEK  (G3708) horao see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G1497) eidolon; an image-fane -- idol's temple. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon

column8: meat offered in sacrifice unto idols.
column9: Neuter of a compound of  (G1497) eidolon and a presumed derivative of  (G2380) thuo; an image-sacrifice, i.e. Part of an idolatrous offering -- (meat, thing that is) offered (in sacrifice, sacrificed) to (unto) idols. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon see GREEK  (G2380) thuo
From  (G1497) eidolon and  (G2999) latreia; image-worship (literally or figuratively) -- idolatry. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon see GREEK  (G2999) latreia
From  (G1497) eidolon and the base of  (G3000) latreuo; an image- (servant or) worshipper (literally or figuratively) -- idolater. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon see GREEK  (G3000) latreuo

column7: an image (for worship), by implication a false god
column9: From  (G1491) eidos; an image (i.e. For worship); by implication, a heathen god, or (plural) the worship of such -- idol. see GREEK  (G1491) eidos
Optative (i.e. English subjunctive) present of  (G1510) eimi (including the other person); might (could, would, or should) be -- mean, + perish, should be, was, were. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
From  (G1487) ei and  (G2532) kai; if also (or even) -- if (that), though. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G2532) kai
Probably from  (G1502) eiko (through the idea of failure); idly, i.e. Without reason (or effect) -- without a cause, (in) vain(-ly). see GREEK  (G1502) eiko
Of uncertain affinity; a score -- twenty.
Apparently a primary verb; properly, to be weak, i.e. Yield -- give place.
Apparently a primary verb (perhaps akin to  (G1502) eiko through the idea of faintness as a copy); to resemble -- be like. see GREEK  (G1502) eiko
From  (G1503) eiko; a likeness, i.e. (literally) statue, profile, or (figuratively) representation, resemblance -- image. see GREEK  (G1503) eiko
From  (G1506) eilikrines; clearness, i.e. (by implication) purity (figuratively) -- sincerity. see GREEK  (G1506) eilikrines
From heile (the sun's ray) and  (G2919) krino; judged by sunlight, i.e. Tested as genuine (figuratively) -- pure, sincere. see GREEK  (G2919) krino
A prolonged form of a primary but defective verb heilo (of the same meaning); to coil or wrap -- roll together. See also  (G1667) helisso. see GREEK  (G1667) helisso

column8: but, except that, if not, save only.
column9: From  (G1487) ei and  (G3361) me; if not -- but, except (that), if not, more than, save (only) that, saving, till. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G3361) me
From  (G1508) ei me and the neuter of  (G5100) tis; if not somewhat -- except. see GREEK  (G1508) ei me see GREEK  (G5100) tis

column8: am, have been, it is I, was.
column9: The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist (used only when emphatic) -- am, have been, X it is I, was. See also  (G1488) ei,  (G1498) eien,  (G1511) einai,  (G1527) heis kath heis,  (G2258) en,  (G2071) esomai,  (G2070) esmen,  (G2075) este,  (G2076) esti,  (G2771) kerdos,  (G2468) isthi,  (G5600) o. see GREEK  (G1488) ei see GREEK  (G1498) eien see GREEK  (G1511) einai see GREEK  (G1527) heis kath heis see GREEK  (G2258) en see GREEK  (G2071) esomai see GREEK  (G2070) esmen see GREEK  (G2075) este see GREEK  (G2076) esti see GREEK  (G2771) kerdos see GREEK  (G2468) isthi see GREEK  (G5600) o

column7: am, was, come, is, there is, to be, was
column8: am, was, come, is, there is, to be, was.
column9: Present infinitive from  (G1510) eimi; to exist -- am, was. Come, is, X lust after, X please well, there is, to be, was. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
From  (G1487) ei and  (G4007) per; if perhaps -- if so be (that), seeing, though. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G4007) per

column7: if by any means, if somehow
column8: if by any means, if somehow
column9: From  (G1487) ei and  (G4458) pos; if somehow -- if by any means. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G4458) pos

column7: to bring to peace, to be at peace
column9: From  (G1515) eirene; to be (act) peaceful -- be at (have, live in) peace, live peaceably. see GREEK  (G1515) eirene
Probably from a primary verb eiro (to join); peace (literally or figuratively); by implication, prosperity -- one, peace, quietness, rest, + set at one again.
From  (G1515) eirene; pacific; by implication, salutary -- peaceable. see GREEK  (G1515) eirene
From  (G1518) eirenopoios; to be a peace-maker, i.e. (figuratively) to harmonize -- make peace. see GREEK  (G1518) eirenopoios
From  (G1518) eirenopoios and  (G4160) poieo; pacificatory, i.e. (subjectively) peaceable -- peacemaker. see GREEK  (G1518) eirenopoios see GREEK  (G4160) poieo

column7: to or into (indicating the point reached or entered, of place, time, purpose, result)
column8: against, among, as, at, backward, before
column9: A primary preposition; to or into (indicating the point reached or entered), of place, time, or (figuratively) purpose (result, etc.); also in adverbial phrases -- (abundant-)ly, against, among, as, at, (back-)ward, before, by, concerning, + continual, + far more exceeding, for (intent, purpose), fore, + forth, in (among, at, unto, -so much that, -to), to the intent that, + of one mind, + never, of, (up-)on, + perish, + set at one again, (so) that, therefore(-unto), throughout, til, to (be, the end, -ward), (here-)until(-to),...ward, (where-)fore, with. Often used in composition with the same general import, but only with verbs (etc.) Expressing motion (literally or figuratively).

column8: man, one another, only, other, some.
column9: (including the neuter (etc.) Hen); a primary numeral; one -- a(-n, -ny, certain), + abundantly, man, one (another), only, other, some. See also  (G1527) heis kath heis,  (G3367) medeis,  (G3391) mia,  (G3762) oudeis. see GREEK  (G1527) heis kath heis see GREEK  (G3367) medeis see GREEK  (G3391) mia see GREEK  (G3762) oudeis
From  (G1519) eis and  (G71) ago; to introduce (literally or figuratively) -- bring in(-to), (+ was to) lead into. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G1519) eis and  (G191) akouo; to listen to -- hear. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G191) akouo

column7: to admit, to receive (into one\'s favor)
column9: From  (G1519) eis and  (G1209) dechomai; to take into one's favor -- receive. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From  (G1519) eis and eimi (to go); to enter -- enter (go) into. see GREEK  (G1519) eis

column8: arise, come into, enter into, go through.
column9: From  (G1519) eis and  (G2064) erchomai; to enter (literally or figuratively) -- X arise, come (in, into), enter in(-to), go in (through). see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G2064) erchomai
3d person plural present indicative of  (G1510) eimi; they are -- agree, are, be, dure, X is, were. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
From  (G1520) heis repeated with  (G2596) kata inserted; severally -- one by one. see GREEK  (G1520) heis see GREEK  (G2596) kata
From  (G1519) eis and  (G2564) kaleo; to invite in -- call in. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G2564) kaleo

column7: an entrance, a means or place of entering
column9: From  (G1519) eis and  (G3598) hodos; an entrance (literally or figuratively) -- coming, enter(-ing) in (to). see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G3598) hodos
From  (G1519) eis and pedao (to leap); to rush in -- run (spring) in. see GREEK  (G1519) eis
From  (G1519) eis and  (G4198) poreuomai; to enter (literally or figuratively) -- come (enter) in, go into. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G4198) poreuomai
From  (G1519) eis and  (G5143) trecho; to hasten inward -- run in. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G5143) trecho
From  (G1519) eis and  (G5342) phero; to carry inward (literally or figuratively) -- bring (in), lead into. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G5342) phero

column7: then, next, therefore (an adverb denoting sequence)
column9: Of uncertain affinity; a particle of succession (in time or logical enumeration), then, moreover -- after that(-ward), furthermore, then. See also  (G1899) epeita. see GREEK  (G1899) epeita
From  (G1487) ei and  (G5037) te; if too -- if, or, whether. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G5037) te

column7: he that, if a man, whether any, whosoever
column8: he that, if a man, whether any, whosoever.
column9: From  (G1487) ei and  (G5100) tis; if any -- he that, if a(-ny) man('s thing, from any, ought), whether any, whosoever. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G5100) tis

column8: out of, from, by means of
column9: A primary preposition denoting origin (the point whence action or motion proceeds), from, out (of place, time, or cause; literal or figurative; direct or remote) -- after, among, X are, at, betwixt(-yond), by (the means of), exceedingly, (+ abundantly above), for(- th), from (among, forth, up), + grudgingly, + heartily, X heavenly, X hereby, + very highly, in,...ly, (because, by reason) of, off (from), on, out among (from, of), over, since, X thenceforth, through, X unto, X vehemently, with(-out). Often used in composition, with the same general import; often of completion.
As if a superlative of hekas (afar); each or every -- any, both, each (one), every (man, one, woman), particularly.
As if from  (G1538) hekastos and  (G5119) tote; at every time -- always. see GREEK  (G1538) hekastos see GREEK  (G5119) tote
Of uncertain affinity; a hundred -- hundred.
From  (G1540) hekaton and  (G2094) etos; centenarian -- hundred years old. see GREEK  (G1540) hekaton see GREEK  (G2094) etos
From  (G1540) hekaton and a presumed derivative of  (G4111) plasso; a hundred times -- hundredfold. see GREEK  (G1540) hekaton see GREEK  (G4111) plasso

column7: a centurion, a captain of one hundred men
column9: Or hekatontarchos hek-at-on'-tar-khos; from  (G1540) hekaton and  (G757) archo; the captain of one hundred men -- centurion. see GREEK  (G1540) hekaton see GREEK  (G757) archo

column8: bring forth, cast forth, drive out, expel.
column9: From  (G1537) ek and  (G906) ballo; to eject (literally or figuratively) -- bring forth, cast (forth, out), drive (out), expel, leave, pluck (pull, take, thrust) out, put forth (out), send away (forth, out). see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G906) ballo
From a compound of  (G1537) ek and the base of  (G939) basis (meaning to go out); an exit (literally or figuratively) -- end, way to escape. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G939) basis

column7: a throwing out, a throwing overboard (of the cargo)
column9: From  (G1544) ekballo; ejection, i.e. (specially) a throwing overboard of the cargo -- + lighten the ship. see GREEK  (G1544) ekballo

From  (G1537) ek and a form of  (G1061) gamisko (compare  (G1548) ekgamisko); to marry off a daughter -- give in marriage. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1061) gamisko see GREEK  (G1548) ekgamisko
From  (G1537) ek and  (G1061) gamisko; the same as  (G1547) ekgamizo -- give in marriage. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1061) gamisko

column7: born of, a descendant, a grandchild
column9: Neuter of a derivative of a compound of  (G1537) ek and  (G1096) ginomai; a descendant, i.e. (specially) grandchild -- nephew. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
From  (G1537) ek and  (G1159) dapanao; to expend (wholly), i.e. (figuratively) exhaust -- spend. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1159) dapanao

column7: to take or receive, by implication to await, expect
column9: From  (G1537) ek and  (G1209) dechomai; to accept from some source, i.e. (by implication) to await -- expect, look (tarry) for, wait (for). see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From  (G1537) ek and  (G1212) delos; wholly evident -- manifest. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1212) delos

column7: to be away from home, absent
column9: From a compound of  (G1537) ek and  (G1218) demos; to emigrate, i.e. (figuratively) vacate or quit -- be absent. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1218) demos

column7: to give up, give out, let out for hire
column9: From  (G1537) ek and  (G1325) didomi; to give forth, i.e. (specially) to lease -- let forth (out). see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From  (G1537) ek and a compound of  (G1223) dia and  (G2233) hegeomai; to narrate through wholly -- declare. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2233) hegeomai
From  (G1558) ekdikos; to vindicate, retaliate, punish -- a (re-)venge. see GREEK  (G1558) ekdikos
From  (G1556) ekdikeo; vindication, retribution -- (a-, re-)venge(-ance), punishment. see GREEK  (G1556) ekdikeo
From  (G1537) ek and  (G1349) dike; carrying justice out, i.e. A punisher -- a (re-)venger. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1349) dike

column7: to pursue out, expel or persecute
column9: From  (G1537) ek and  (G1377) dioko; to pursue out, i.e. Expel or persecute implacably -- persecute. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1377) dioko
From  (G1537) ek and a derivative of  (G1325) didomi; given out or over, i.e. Surrendered -- delivered. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From  (G1551) ekdechomai; expectation -- looking foreign see GREEK  (G1551) ekdechomai

column7: to take off, to put off
column9: From  (G1537) ek and the base of  (G1416) duno; to cause to sink out of, i.e. (specially as of clothing) to divest -- strip, take off from, unclothe. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G1416) duno
Of uncertain affinity; there; by extension, thither -- there, thither(-ward), (to) yonder (place).

column8: from that place, from thence, there.
column9: From  (G1563) ekei; thence -- from that place, (from) thence, there. see GREEK  (G1563) ekei

column7: that one (or neut. that thing), often intensified by the article preceding
column8: he, it, the other, that very
column9: From  (G1563) ekei; that one (or (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed -- he, it, the other (same), selfsame, that (same, very), X their, X them, they, this, those. See also  (G3778) houtos. see GREEK  (G1563) ekei see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
From  (G1563) ekei; thither -- there. see GREEK  (G1563) ekei

From  (G1537) ek and  (G2212) zeteo; to search out, i.e. (figuratively)investigate, crave, demand, (by Hebraism) worship -- en- (re-)quire, seek after (carefully, diligently). see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2212) zeteo
From  (G1569) ekthambos; to astonish utterly -- affright, greatly (sore) amaze. see GREEK  (G1569) ekthambos
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2285) thambos; utterly astounded -- greatly wondering. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2285) thambos
From  (G1537) ek and a derivative of  (G5087) tithemi; put out, i.e. Exposed to perish -- cast out. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2508) kathairo; to cleanse thoroughly -- purge (out). see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2508) kathairo
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2545) kaio; to inflame deeply -- burn. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2545) kaio
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2556) kakos; to be (bad or) weak, i.e. (by implication) to fail (in heart) -- faint, be weary. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2556) kakos
From  (G1537) ek and the base of  (G2759) kentron; to transfix -- pierce. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2759) kentron
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2806) klao; to exscind -- break off. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2806) klao
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2808) kleio; to shut out (literally or figuratively) -- exclude. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2808) kleio

From a compound of  (G1537) ek and a derivative of  (G2564) kaleo; a calling out, i.e. (concretely) a popular meeting, especially a religious congregation (Jewish synagogue, or Christian community of members on earth or saints in heaven or both) -- assembly, church. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2564) kaleo

column7: to deviate, to turn away (from someone or something)
column8: avoid, eschew, go out of the way.
column9: From  (G1537) ek and  (G2827) klino; to deviate, i.e. (absolutely) to shun (literally or figuratively), or (relatively) to decline (from piety) -- avoid, eschew, go out of the way. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2827) klino
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2860) kolumbao; to escape by swimming -- swim out. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2860) kolumbao
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2865) komizo; to bear forth (to burial) -- carry out. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2865) komizo

column7: to cut off, cut down, cut out, to frustrate
column8: cut down, cut out, hew down, hinder.
column9: From  (G1537) ek and  (G2875) kopto; to exscind; figuratively, to frustrate -- cut down (off, out), hew down, hinder. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2875) kopto

column7: to hang from, hang upon (the lips of a speaker), to listen closely
column9: Middle voice from  (G1537) ek and  (G2910) kremannumi; to hang upon the lips of a speaker, i.e. Listen closely -- be very attentive. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2910) kremannumi
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2980) laleo; to divulge -- tell. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2980) laleo
From  (G1537) ek and  (G2989) lampo; to be resplendent -- shine forth. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2989) lampo

A primary preposition denoting (fixed) position (in place, time or state), and (by implication) instrumentality (medially or constructively), i.e. A relation of rest (intermediate between  (G1519) eis and  (G1537) ek); "in," at, (up-)on, by, etc. -- about, after, against, + almost, X altogether, among, X as, at, before, between, (here-)by (+ all means), for (... Sake of), + give self wholly to, (here-)in(-to, -wardly), X mightily, (because) of, (up-)on, (open-)ly, X outwardly, one, X quickly, X shortly, (speedi-)ly, X that, X there(-in, -on), through(-out), (un-)to(-ward), under, when, where(-with), while, with(-in). Often used in compounds, with substantially the same import; rarely with verbs of motion, and then not to indicate direction, except (elliptically) by a separate (and different) preposition. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G1537) ek
