From  (G1832) exesti (in the sense of ability); privilege, i.e. (subjectively) force, capacity, competency, freedom, or (objectively) mastery (concretely, magistrate, superhuman, potentate, token of control), delegated influence -- authority, jurisdiction, liberty, power, right, strength. see GREEK  (G1832) exesti

column8: exercise authority upon, bring under the power of.
column9: From  (G1849) exousia; to control -- exercise authority upon, bring under the (have) power of. see GREEK  (G1849) exousia
From a compound of  (G1537) ek and  (G2192) echo (meaning to stand out); prominence (figuratively) -- principal. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From  (G1853) exupnos; to waken -- awake out of sleep. see GREEK  (G1853) exupnos
From  (G1537) ek and  (G5258) hupnos; awake -- X out of sleep. see GREEK  (G1537) ek see GREEK  (G5258) hupnos
Adverb from  (G1537) ek; out(-side, of doors), literally or figuratively -- away, forth, (with-)out (of, -ward), strange. see GREEK  (G1537) ek
From  (G1854) exo; external(-ly) -- out(-side, -ward, - wardly), (from) without. see GREEK  (G1854) exo
Or exotho ex-o'-tho from  (G1537) ek and otheo (to push); to expel; by implication, to propel -- drive out, thrust in. see GREEK  (G1537) ek
Comparative of  (G1854) exo; exterior -- outer. see GREEK  (G1854) exo
From  (G1859) heorte; to observe a festival -- keep the feast. see GREEK  (G1859) heorte
Of uncertain affinity; a festival -- feast, holyday.
From  (G1861) epaggello; an announcement (for information, assent or pledge; especially a divine assurance of good) -- message, promise. see GREEK  (G1861) epaggello

From  (G1909) epi and the base of  (G32) aggelos; to announce upon (reflexively), i.e. (by implication) to engage to do something, to assert something respecting oneself -- profess, (make) promise. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G32) aggelos
From  (G1861) epaggello; a self-committal (by assurance of conferring some good) -- promise. see GREEK  (G1861) epaggello
From  (G1909) epi and  (G71) ago; to superinduce, i.e. Inflict (an evil), charge (a crime) -- bring upon. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G1909) epi and  (G75) agonizomai; to struggle for -- earnestly contend foreign see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G75) agonizomai
From  (G1909) epi and athroizo (to assemble); to accumulate -- gather thick together. see GREEK  (G1909) epi

column7: praiseworthy, Epaenetus, a Christian of Rome
column9: From  (G1867) epaineo; praised; Epaenetus, a Christian -- Epenetus. see GREEK  (G1867) epaineo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G134) aineo; to applaud -- commend, laud, praise. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G134) aineo
From  (G1909) epi and the base of  (G134) aineo; laudation; concretely, a commendable thing -- praise. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G134) aineo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G142) airo; to raise up (literally or figuratively) -- exalt self, poise (lift, take) up. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G142) airo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G153) aischunomai; to feel shame for something -- be ashamed. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G153) aischunomai
From  (G1909) epi and  (G154) aiteo; to ask for -- beg. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G154) aiteo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G190) akoloutheo; to accompany -- follow (after). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G190) akoloutheo

column7: to listen to, to hearken to
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G191) akouo; to hearken (favorably) to -- hear. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G191) akouo
From  (G1909) epi and the base of  (G202) akroates; to listen (intently) to -- hear. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G202) akroates
From  (G1909) epi and  (G302) an; a particle of indefinite contemporaneousness; whenever, as soon as -- when. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G302) an
Neuter of a presumed compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G318) anagke; (adverbially) on necessity, i.e. Necessarily -- necessary. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G318) anagke

column7: to put out (to sea), to return
column8: put out to sea, thrust out, return.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G321) anago; to lead up on, i.e. (technical) to put out (to sea); (intransitively) to return -- launch (thrust) out, return. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G321) anago
From  (G1909) epi and  (G363) anamimnesko; to remind of -- put in mind. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G363) anamimnesko
Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G373) anapano; to settle on; literally (remain) or figuratively (rely) -- rest in (upon). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G373) anapano
From  (G1909) epi and  (G424) anerchomai; to come up on, i.e. Return -- come again, return. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G424) anerchomai
Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G450) anistemi; to stand up on, i.e. (figuratively) to attack -- rise up against. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G450) anistemi
From a compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G461) anorthoo; a straightening up again, i.e. (figuratively) rectification (reformation) -- correction. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G461) anorthoo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G507) ano; up above, i.e. Over or on (of place, amount, rank, etc.) -- above, more than, (up-)on, over. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G507) ano
From  (G1909) epi and  (G714) arkeo; to avail for, i.e. Help -- relieve. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G714) arkeo

From a compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G757) archo (meaning a governor of a district, "eparch"); a special region of government, i.e. A Roman pr?Fecture -- province. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G757) archo
From  (G1909) epi and an equivalent of  (G833) aule; a hut over the head, i.e. A dwelling -- habitation. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G833) aule

From  (G1909) epi and  (G839) aurion; occurring on the succeeding day, i.e. ( (G2250) hemera being implied) to-morrow -- day following, morrow, next day (after). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G839) aurion see GREEK  (G2250) hemera

From  (G1909) epi and  (G846) autos and (the dative case singular of) a derivative of phor (a thief); in theft itself, i.e. (by analogy) in actual crime -- in the very act. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G846) autos
Contracted from  (G1891) Epaphroditos; Epaphras, a Christian -- Epaphras. see GREEK  (G1891) Epaphroditos
From  (G1909) epi and  (G875) aphrizo; to foam upon, i.e. (figuratively) to exhibit (a vile passion) -- foam out. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G875) aphrizo
From  (G1909) epi (in the sense of devoted to) and Aphrodite (Venus); Epaphroditus, a Christian -- Epaphroditus. Compare  (G1889) Epaphras. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1889) Epaphras
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1453) egeiro; to rouse upon, i.e. (figuratively) to excite against -- raise, stir up. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1453) egeiro

From  (G1909) epi and  (G1487) ei; thereupon, i.e. Since (of time or cause) -- because, else, for that (then, -asmuch as), otherwise, seeing that, since, when. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1487) ei

column8: after that, because, for, seeing, since.
column9: From  (G1893) epei and  (G1211) de; since now, i.e. (of time) when, or (of cause) whereas -- after that, because, for (that, -asmuch as), seeing, since. see GREEK  (G1893) epei see GREEK  (G1211) de
From  (G1894) epeide and  (G4007) per; since indeed (of cause) -- forasmuch. see GREEK  (G1894) epeide see GREEK  (G4007) per
And other moods and persons of the same tense; from  (G1909) epi and  (G1492) eido; to regard (favorably or otherwise) -- behold, look upon. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1492) eido
From  (G1893) epei and  (G4007) per; since indeed (of cause) -- seeing. see GREEK  (G1893) epei see GREEK  (G4007) per
From a compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G1521) eisago; a superintroduction -- bringing in. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1521) eisago
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1534) eita; thereafter -- after that(-ward), then. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1534) eita
From  (G1909) epi and (the accusative case plural neuter of)  (G1565) ekeinos; upon those parts of, i.e. On the further side of -- beyond. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1565) ekeinos

column7: to extend, mid. to stretch forward
column9: Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G1614) ekteino; to stretch (oneself) forward upon -- reach forth. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1614) ekteino
Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G1746) enduo; to invest upon oneself -- be clothed upon. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1746) enduo
From  (G1902) ependuomai; a wrapper, i.e. Outer garment -- fisher's coat. see GREEK  (G1902) ependuomai
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2064) erchomai; to supervene, i.e. Arrive, occur, impend, attack, (figuratively) influence -- come (in, upon). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2064) erchomai
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2065) erotao; to ask for, i.e. Inquire, seek -- ask (after, questions), demand, desire, question. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2065) erotao
From  (G1905) eperotao; an inquiry -- answer. see GREEK  (G1905) eperotao

column7: to hold fast, to hold toward, to stop
column8: take heed unto, hold forth, mark, stay.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G2192) echo; to hold upon, i.e. (by implication) to retain; (by extension) to detain; (with implication, of  (G3563) nous) to pay attention to -- give (take) heed unto, hold forth, mark, stay. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2192) echo see GREEK  (G3563) nous
From a comparative of  (G1909) epi and (probably) areia (threats); to insult, slander -- use despitefully, falsely accuse. see GREEK  (G1909) epi

column8: above, after, against, among, as long as
column9: A primary preposition; properly, meaning superimposition (of time, place, order, etc.), as a relation of distribution (with the genitive case), i.e. Over, upon, etc.; of rest (with the dative case) at, on, etc.; of direction (with the accusative case) towards, upon, etc. -- about (the times), above, after, against, among, as long as (touching), at, beside, X have charge of, (be-, (where-))fore, in (a place, as much as, the time of, -to), (because) of, (up-)on (behalf of), over, (by, for) the space of, through(-out), (un-)to(-ward), with. In compounds it retains essentially the same import, at, upon, etc. (literally or figuratively).

column7: to go aboard, to go up to
column8: come into, enter into, go abroad, sit upon, take ship.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and the base of  (G939) basis; to walk upon, i.e. Mount, ascend, embark, arrive -- come (into), enter into, go abroad, sit upon, take ship. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G939) basis

column7: to throw over, to throw oneself
column8: fall, lay on, stretch forth, think on.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G906) ballo; to throw upon (literal or figurative, transitive or reflexive; usually with more or less force); specially (with  (G1438) heautou implied) to reflect; impersonally, to belong to -- beat into, cast (up-)on, fall, lay (on), put (unto), stretch forth, think on. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G906) ballo see GREEK  (G1438) heautou

From  (G1909) epi and  (G916) bareo; to be heavy upon, i.e. (pecuniarily) to be expensive to; figuratively, to be severe towards -- be chargeable to, overcharge. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G916) bareo

From  (G1909) epi and a reduplicated derivative of the base of  (G939) basis (compare  (G307) anabibazo); to cause to mount (an animal) -- set on. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G939) basis see GREEK  (G307) anabibazo

column8: look upon, regard, have respect for.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G991) blepo; to gaze at (with favor, pity or partiality) -- look upon, regard, have respect to. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G991) blepo

column7: that which is put on, a patch
column9: From  (G1911) epiballo; a patch -- piece. see GREEK  (G1911) epiballo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G994) boao; to exclaim against -- cry. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G994) boao
From a presumed compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G1014) boulomai; a plan against someone, i.e. A plot -- laying (lying) in wait. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1014) boulomai
From  (G1909) epi and a derivative of  (G1062) gamos; to form affinity with, i.e. (specially) in a levirate way -- marry. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1062) gamos
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1093) ge; worldly (physically or morally) -- earthly, in earth, terrestrial. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1093) ge
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1096) ginomai; to arrive upon, i.e. Spring up (as a wind) -- blow. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai

From  (G1909) epi and  (G1097) ginosko; to know upon some mark, i.e. Recognize; by implication, to become fully acquainted with, to acknowledge -- (ac-, have, take)know(-ledge, well), perceive. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko
From  (G1921) epiginosko; recognition, i.e. (by implication) full discernment, acknowledgement -- (ac-)knowledge(-ing, - ment). see GREEK  (G1921) epiginosko
From  (G1924) epigrapho; an inscription -- superscription. see GREEK  (G1924) epigrapho
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1125) grapho; to inscribe (physically or mentally) -- inscription, write in (over, thereon). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1125) grapho
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1166) deiknuo; to exhibit (physically or mentally) -- shew. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1166) deiknuo

column7: to accept as true, to receive besides
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G1209) dechomai; to admit (as a guest or (figuratively) teacher) -- receive. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai

From a compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G1218) demos; to make oneself at home, i.e. (by extension) to reside (in a foreign country) -- (be) dwelling (which were) there, stranger. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1218) demos
Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G1299) diatasso; to appoint besides, i.e. Supplement (as a codicil) -- add to. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1299) diatasso
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1325) didomi; to give over (by hand or surrender) -- deliver unto, give, let (+ (her drive)), offer. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From  (G1909) epi and a derivative of  (G3717) orthos; to straighten further, i.e. (figuratively) arrange additionally -- set in order. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3717) orthos
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1416) duno; to set fully (as the sun) -- go down. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1416) duno
From  (G1933) epieikes; suitableness, i.e. (by implication) equity, mildness -- clemency, gentleness. see GREEK  (G1933) epieikes
From  (G1909) epi and  (G1503) eiko; appropriate, i.e. (by implication) mild -- gentle, moderation, patient. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1503) eiko
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2212) zeteo; to search (inquire) for; intensively, to demand, to crave -- desire, enquire, seek (after, for). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2212) zeteo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2288) thanatos; doomed to death -- appointed to death. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2288) thanatos
From  (G2007) epitithemi; an imposition (of hands officially) -- laying (putting) on. see GREEK  (G2007) epitithemi
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2372) thumos; to set the heart upon, i.e. Long for (rightfully or otherwise) -- covet, desire, would fain, lust (after). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2372) thumos
From  (G1937) epithumeo; a craver see GREEK  (G1937) epithumeo
From  (G1937) epithumeo; a longing (especially for what is forbidden) -- concupiscence, desire, lust (after). see GREEK  (G1937) epithumeo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2523) kathizo; to seat upon -- set on. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2523) kathizo

Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G2564) kaleo; to entitle; by implication, to invoke (for aid, worship, testimony, decision, etc.) -- appeal (unto), call (on, upon), surname. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2564) kaleo
From  (G1943) epikalupto; a covering, i.e. (figuratively) pretext -- cloke. see GREEK  (G1943) epikalupto
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2572) kalupto; to conceal, i.e. (figuratively) forgive -- cover. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2572) kalupto
From  (G1909) epi and a derivative of  (G2672) kataraomai; imprecated, i.e. Execrable -- accursed. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2672) kataraomai

From  (G1909) epi and  (G2749) keimai; to rest upon (literally or figuratively) -- impose, be instant, (be) laid (there-, up-)on, (when) lay (on), lie (on), press upon. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2749) keimai
From Epikouros (compare  (G1947) epikouria) (a noted philosopher); an Epicurean or follower of Epicurus -- Epicurean. see GREEK  (G1947) epikouria
From a compound of  (G1909) epi and a (prolonged) form of the base of  (G2877) korasion (in the sense of servant); assistance -- help. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2877) korasion
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2919) krino; to adjudge -- give sentence. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2919) krino

Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G2983) lambano; to seize (for help, injury, attainment, or any other purpose; literally or figuratively) -- catch, lay hold (up-)on, take (by, hold of, on). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2983) lambano
Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G2990) lanthano; to lose out of mind; by implication, to neglect -- (be) forget(-ful of). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2990) lanthano

column7: to call or name, to choose
column9: Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and  (G3004) lego; to surname, select -- call, choose. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3004) lego
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3007) leipo; to leave upon, i.e. (figuratively) to be insufficient for -- fail. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3007) leipo
From a derivative of  (G1950) epilanthanomai; negligence -- X forgetful. see GREEK  (G1950) epilanthanomai
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3062) loipoy; left over, i.e. Remaining -- rest. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3062) loipoy
From  (G1956) epiluo; explanation, i.e. Application -- interpretation. see GREEK  (G1956) epiluo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3089) luo; to solve further, i.e. (figuratively) to explain, decide -- determine, expound. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3089) luo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3140) martureo; to attest further, i.e. Corroborate -- testify. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3140) martureo
From  (G1959) epimeleomai; carefulness, i.e. Kind attention (hospitality) -- + refresh self. see GREEK  (G1959) epimeleomai
Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and the same as  (G3199) melo; to care for (physically or otherwise) -- take care of. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3199) melo
Adverb from a derivative of  (G1959) epimeleomai; carefully -- diligently. see GREEK  (G1959) epimeleomai
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3306) meno; to stay over, i.e. Remain (figuratively, persevere) -- abide (in), continue (in), tarry. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3306) meno
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3506) neuo; to nod at, i.e. (by implication) to assent -- consent. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3506) neuo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3563) nous; attention of the mind, i.e. (by implication) purpose -- thought. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3563) nous
From  (G1965) epiorkos; to commit perjury -- forswear self. see GREEK  (G1965) epiorkos
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3727) horkos; on oath, i.e. (falsely) a forswearer -- perjured person. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3727) horkos

Feminine singular participle of a comparative of  (G1909) epi and heimi (to go); supervening, i.e. ( (G2250) hemera or  (G3571) nux being expressed or implied) the ensuing day or night -- following, next. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2250) hemera see GREEK  (G3571) nux

column7: for the coming day, for subsistence
column9: Perhaps from the same as  (G1966) epiousa; tomorrow's; but more probably from  (G1909) epi and a derivative of the present participle feminine of  (G1510) eimi; for subsistence, i.e. Needful -- daily. see GREEK  (G1966) epiousa see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column8: fall into, lie on, press upon.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G4098) pipto; to embrace (with affection) or seize (with more or less violence; literally or figuratively) -- fall into (on, upon) lie on, press upon. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4098) pipto

column7: to strike at, to rebuke (with words)
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G4141) plesso; to chastise, i.e. (with words) to upbraid -- rebuke. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4141) plesso
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4155) pnigo; to throttle upon, i.e. (figuratively) overgrow -- choke. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4155) pnigo
From  (G1909) epi and potheo (to yearn); to dote upon, i.e. Intensely crave possession (lawfully or wrongfully) -- (earnestly) desire (greatly), (greatly) long (after), lust. see GREEK  (G1909) epi
From  (G1971) epipotheo; a longing for -- earnest (vehement) desire. see GREEK  (G1971) epipotheo
From  (G1909) epi and a derivative of the latter part of  (G1971) epipotheo; yearned upon, i.e. Greatly loved -- longed foreign see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G1971) epipotheo
From  (G1971) epipotheo; intense longing -- great desire. see GREEK  (G1971) epipotheo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4198) poreuomai; to journey further, i.e. Travel on (reach) -- come. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4198) poreuomai
From  (G1909) epi and the base of  (G4476) rhaphis; to stitch upon, i.e. Fasten with the needle -- sew on. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4476) rhaphis
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4496) rhipto; to throw upon (literally or figuratively) -- cast upon. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4496) rhipto
From  (G1909) epi and some form of the base of  (G4591) semaino; remarkable, i.e. (figuratively) eminent -- notable, of note. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4591) semaino
From a compound of  (G1909) epi and a derivative of  (G4621) sitos; a provisioning, i.e. (concretely) food -- victuals. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4621) sitos

column7: to inspect,  to go to see
column9: Middle voice from  (G1909) epi and the base of  (G4649) skopos; to inspect, i.e. (by implication) to select; by extension, to go to see, relieve -- look out, visit. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4649) skopos
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4637) skenoo; to tent upon, i.e. (figuratively) abide with -- rest upon. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4637) skenoo

From  (G1909) epi and a derivative of  (G4639) skia; to cast a shade upon, i.e. (by analogy) to envelop in a haze of brilliancy; figuratively, to invest with preternatural influence -- overshadow. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4639) skia

column7: to look upon, to care for
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G4648) skopeo; to oversee; by implication, to beware -- look diligently, take the oversight. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4648) skopeo

From  (G1980) episkeptomai; inspection (for relief); by implication, superintendence; specially, the Christian "episcopate" -- the office of a "bishop", bishoprick, visitation. see GREEK  (G1980) episkeptomai

From  (G1909) epi and  (G4649) skopos (in the sense of  (G1983) episkopeo); a superintendent, i.e. Christian officer in genitive case charge of a (or the) church (literally or figuratively) -- bishop, overseer. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4649) skopos see GREEK  (G1983) episkopeo

column7: to draw over, to become as uncircumcised
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G4685) spao; to draw over, i.e. (with  (G203) akrobustia implied) efface the mark of circumcision (by recovering with the foreskin) -- become uncircumcised. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4685) spao see GREEK  (G203) akrobustia

Apparently a middle voice of  (G2186) ephistemi (with  (G3563) nous implied); to put the mind upon, i.e. Comprehend, or be acquainted with -- know, understand. see GREEK  (G2186) ephistemi see GREEK  (G3563) nous
From  (G1909) epi and a presumed derivative of  (G2476) histemi; an appointee over, i.e. Commander (teacher) -- master. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2476) histemi

From  (G1909) epi and  (G4724) stello; to enjoin (by writing), i.e. (genitive case) to communicate by letter (for any purpose) -- write (a letter, unto). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4724) stello
From  (G1987) epistamai; intelligent -- endued with knowledge. see GREEK  (G1987) epistamai
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4741) sterizo; to support further, i.e. Reestablish -- confirm, strengthen. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4741) sterizo
From  (G1989) epistello; a written message -- "epistle," letter. see GREEK  (G1989) epistello
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4750) stoma; to put something over the mouth, i.e. (figuratively) to silence -- stop mouths. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4750) stoma
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4762) strepho; to revert (literally, figuratively or morally) -- come (go) again, convert, (re-)turn (about, again). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4762) strepho
From  (G1994) epistrepho; reversion, i.e. Morally, revolution -- conversion. see GREEK  (G1994) epistrepho
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4863) sunago; to collect upon the same place -- gather (together). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4863) sunago
From  (G1996) episunago; a complete collection; especially a Christian meeting (for worship) -- assembling (gathering) together. see GREEK  (G1996) episunago
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4936) suntrecho; to hasten together upon one place (or a particular occasion) -- come running together. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4936) suntrecho

From the middle voice of a compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G4921) sunistao; a conspiracy, i.e. Concourse (riotous or friendly) -- that which cometh upon, + raising up. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4921) sunistao
From a compound of  (G1909) epi and sphallo (to trip); figuratively, insecure -- dangerous. see GREEK  (G1909) epi
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2480) ischuo; to avail further, i.e. (figuratively) insist stoutly -- be the more fierce. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2480) ischuo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G4987) soreuo; to accumulate further, i.e. (figuratively) seek additionally -- heap. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G4987) soreuo
From  (G2004) epitasso; an injunction or decree; by implication, authoritativeness -- authority, commandment. see GREEK  (G2004) epitasso
From  (G1909) epi and  (G5021) tasso; to arrange upon, i.e. Order -- charge, command, injoin. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5021) tasso

From  (G1909) epi and  (G5055) teleo; to fulfill further (or completely), i.e. Execute; by implication, to terminate, undergo -- accomplish, do, finish, (make) (perfect), perform(X -ance). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5055) teleo
From epitedes (enough); serviceable, i.e. (by implication) requisite -- things which are needful.

column7: to lay upon, to place upon
column8: add unto, lay upon, put upon.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G5087) tithemi; to impose (in a friendly or hostile sense) -- add unto, lade, lay upon, put (up) on, set on (up), + surname, X wound. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi

column7: to honor, to mete out due measure, to censure
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G5091) timao; to tax upon, i.e. Censure or admonish; by implication, forbid -- (straitly) charge, rebuke. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5091) timao

From a compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G5092) time; properly, esteem, i.e. Citizenship; used (in the sense of  (G2008) epitimao) of a penalty -- punishment. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5092) time see GREEK  (G2008) epitimao

column7: to turn to, entrust, to permit
column9: From  (G1909) epi and the base of  (G5157) trope; to turn over (transfer), i.e. Allow -- give leave (liberty, license), let, permit, suffer. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5157) trope
From  (G2010) epitrepo; permission, i.e. (by implication) full power -- commission. see GREEK  (G2010) epitrepo

From  (G1909) epi and  (G5158) tropos (in the sense of  (G2011) epitrope); a commissioner, i.e. Domestic manager, guardian -- steward, tutor. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5158) tropos see GREEK  (G2011) epitrope
From  (G1909) epi and  (G5177) tugchano; to chance upon, i.e. (by implication) to attain -- obtain. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5177) tugchano
From  (G1909) epi and  (G5316) phaino; to shine upon, i.e. Become (literally) visible or (figuratively) known -- appear, give light. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5316) phaino
From  (G2016) epiphanes; a manifestation, i.e. (specially) the advent of Christ (past or future) -- appearing, brightness. see GREEK  (G2016) epiphanes
From  (G2014) epiphaino; conspicuous, i.e. (figuratively) memorable -- notable. see GREEK  (G2014) epiphaino
A form of  (G2014) epiphaino; to illuminate (figuratively) -- give light. see GREEK  (G2014) epiphaino

From  (G1909) epi and  (G5342) phero; to bear upon (or further), i.e. Adduce (personally or judicially (accuse, inflict)), superinduce -- add, bring (against), take. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5342) phero
From  (G1909) epi and  (G5455) phoneo; to call at something, i.e. Exclaim -- cry (against), give a shout. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5455) phoneo
A form of  (G2017) epiphauo; to begin to grow light -- begin to dawn, X draw on. see GREEK  (G2017) epiphauo

column7: to put one\'s hand to, to attempt
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G5495) cheir; to put the hand upon, i.e. Undertake -- go about, take in hand (upon). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5495) cheir
From  (G1909) epi and cheo (to pour); --to pour upon -- pour in. see GREEK  (G1909) epi

From  (G1909) epi and  (G5524) choregeo; to furnish besides, i.e. Fully supply, (figuratively) aid or contribute -- add, minister (nourishment, unto). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5524) choregeo
From  (G2023) epichoregeo; contribution -- supply. see GREEK  (G2023) epichoregeo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G5548) chrio; to smear over -- anoint. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G5548) chrio
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3618) oikodomeo; to build upon, i.e. (figuratively) to rear up -- build thereon (thereupon, on, upon). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3618) oikodomeo
From  (G1909) epi and okello (to urge); to drive upon the shore, i.e. To beach a vessel -- run aground. see GREEK  (G1909) epi
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3687) onomazo; to name further, i.e. Denominate -- call. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3687) onomazo
From  (G1909) epi and a derivative of  (G3700) optanomai; to inspect, i.e. Watch -- behold. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
From  (G1909) epi and a presumed derivative of  (G3700) optanomai; a looker-on -- eye-witness. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
From  (G2036) epo; a word -- X say. see GREEK  (G2036) epo
From  (G1909) epi and  (G3772) ouranos; above the sky -- celestial, (in) heaven(-ly), high. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G3772) ouranos
A primary number; seven -- seven.
Adverb from  (G2033) hepta; seven times -- seven times. see GREEK  (G2033) hepta
From  (G2034) heptakis and  (G5507) chilioi; seven times a thousand -- seven thousand. see GREEK  (G2034) heptakis see GREEK  (G5507) chilioi

A primary verb (used only in the definite past tense, the others being borrowed from  (G2046) ereo,  (G4483) rheo, and  (G5346) phemi); to speak or say (by word or writing) -- answer, bid, bring word, call, command, grant, say (on), speak, tell. Compare  (G3004) lego. see GREEK  (G2046) ereo see GREEK  (G4483) rheo see GREEK  (G5346) phemi see GREEK  (G3004) lego

column7: beloved, Erastus, the name of two Christians
column9: From erao (to love); beloved; Erastus, a Christian -- Erastus.

column8: commit, do, labor for, minister about
column9: Middle voice from  (G2041) ergon; to toil (as a task, occupation, etc.), (by implication) effect, be engaged in or with, etc. -- commit, do, labor for, minister about, trade (by), work. see GREEK  (G2041) ergon
From  (G2040) ergates; occupation; by implication, profit, pains -- craft, diligence, gain, work. see GREEK  (G2040) ergates
From  (G2041) ergon; a toiler; figuratively, a teacher -- labourer, worker(-men). see GREEK  (G2041) ergon
From a primary (but obsolete) ergo (to work); toil (as an effort or occupation); by implication, an act -- deed, doing, labour, work.
From a presumed prolonged form of  (G2054) eris; to stimulate (especially to anger) -- provoke. see GREEK  (G2054) eris
Of obscure affinity; to prop, i.e. (reflexively) get fast -- stick fast.
Of uncertain affinity; to belch, i.e. (figuratively) to speak out -- utter.
Apparently from  (G2046) ereo (through the idea of inquiry); to seek, i.e. (figuratively) to investigate -- search. see GREEK  (G2046) ereo
Probably a fuller form of  (G4483) rheo; an alternate for  (G2036) epo in certain tenses; to utter, i.e. Speak or say -- call, say, speak (of), tell. see GREEK  (G4483) rheo see GREEK  (G2036) epo
From  (G2048) eremos; solitude (concretely) -- desert, wilderness. see GREEK  (G2048) eremos
Of uncertain affinity; lonesome, i.e. (by implication) waste (usually as a noun,  (G5561) chora being implied) -- desert, desolate, solitary, wilderness. see GREEK  (G5561) chora
From  (G2048) eremos; to lay waste (literally or figuratively) -- (bring to, make) desolate(-ion), come to nought. see GREEK  (G2048) eremos
From  (G2049) eremoo; despoliation -- desolation. see GREEK  (G2049) eremoo
From  (G2054) eris; to wrangle -- strive. see GREEK  (G2054) eris
Perhaps as the same as  (G2042) erethizo; properly, intrigue, i.e. (by implication) faction -- contention(-ious), strife. see GREEK  (G2042) erethizo
Of obscure affinity; wool -- wool.
Of uncertain affinity; a quarrel, i.e. (by implication) wrangling -- contention, debate, strife, variance.
From  (G2056) eriphos; a kidling, i.e. (genitive case) goat (symbolically, wicked person) -- goat. see GREEK  (G2056) eriphos
Perhaps from the same as  (G2053) erion (through the idea of hairiness); a kid or (genitive case) goat -- goat, kid. see GREEK  (G2053) erion
Probably from  (G2060) Hermes; Hermas, a Christian -- Hermas. see GREEK  (G2060) Hermes
From the same as  (G2059) hermeneuo; translation -- interpretation. see GREEK  (G2059) hermeneuo
From a presumed derivative of  (G2060) Hermes (as the god of language); to translate -- interpret. see GREEK  (G2060) Hermes

column7: Hermes, the name of a Greek  god and a Christian at Rome
column9: Perhaps from  (G2046) ereo; Hermes, the name of the messenger of the Greek deities; also of a Christian -- Hermes, Mercury. see GREEK  (G2046) ereo

column7: born of Hermes, Hermogenes, one who deserted Paul
column9: From  (G2060) Hermes and  (G1096) ginomai; born of Hermes; Hermogenes, an apostate Christian -- Hermogenes. see GREEK  (G2060) Hermes see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
Neuter of a derivative of herpo (to creep); a reptile, i.e. (by Hebraism (compare  (H7431) remes)) a small animal -- creeping thing, serpent. see HEBREW  (H7431) remes
Of uncertain affinity; red, i.e. (with  (G2281) thalassa) the Red Sea -- red. see GREEK  (G2281) thalassa

column8: accompany, appear, bring, come, enter, fall out, go, grow
column9: Middle voice of a primary verb (used only in the present and imperfect tenses, the others being supplied by a kindred (middle voice) eleuthomai el-yoo'-thom-ahee, or (active) eltho el'-tho, which do not otherwise occur) to come or go (in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively) -- accompany, appear, bring, come, enter, fall out, go, grow, X light, X next, pass, resort, be set.

Apparently from  (G2046) ereo (compare  (G2045) ereunao); to interrogate; by implication, to request -- ask, beseech, desire, intreat, pray. Compare  (G4441) punthanomai. see GREEK  (G2046) ereo see GREEK  (G2045) ereunao see GREEK  (G4441) punthanomai
From hennumi (to clothe); dress -- apparel, clothing, raiment, robe.
From a derivative of  (G2066) esthes; clothing (concretely) -- government. see GREEK  (G2066) esthes
Strengthened for a primary edo (to eat); used only in certain tenses, the rest being supplied by  (G5315) phago; to eat (usually literal) -- devour, eat, live. see GREEK  (G5315) phago
Of Hebrew origin (probably for  (H454) Elyhow'eynay); Esli, an Israelite -- Esli. see HEBREW  (H454) Elyhow'eynay

column7: are, be, have our being, have hope
column8: are, be, have our being, have hope.
column9: First person plural indicative of  (G1510) eimi; we are -- are, be, have our being, X have hope, + (the gospel) was (preached unto) us. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column7: should be, shall come to pass, may have
column8: should be, shall come to pass, may have
column9: Future of  (G1510) eimi; will be -- shall (should) be (have), (shall) come (to pass), X may have, X fall, what would follow, X live long, X sojourn. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column7: a mirror (i.e. an object for looking into)
column9: From  (G1519) eis and a presumed derivative of  (G3700) optanomai; a mirror (for looking into) -- glass. Compare  (G2734) katoptrizomai. see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai see GREEK  (G2734) katoptrizomai
Feminine of an adjective hesperos (evening); the eve ( (G5610) hora being implied) -- evening(-tide). see GREEK  (G5610) hora
Of Hebrew origin ( (H2696) Chetsrown); Esrom (i.e. Chetsron), an Israelite -- Esrom. see HEBREW  (H2696) Chetsrown
Second person plural present indicative of  (G1510) eimi; ye are -- be, have been, belong. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

Third person singular present indicative of  (G1510) eimi; he (she or it) is; also (with neuter plural) they are -- are, be(-long), call, X can(-not), come, consisteth, X dure for a while, + follow, X have, (that) is (to say), make, meaneth, X must needs, + profit, + remaineth, + wrestle. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
Second person singular present imperative of  (G1510) eimi; be thou; also estosan es'-to-san, third person of the same let them be -- be. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
A superlative probably from  (G2192) echo (in the sense of contiguity); farthest, final (of place or time) -- ends of, last, latter end, lowest, uttermost. see GREEK  (G2192) echo
Adverb from  (G2078) eschatos; finally, i.e. (with  (G2192) echo) at the extremity of life -- point of death. see GREEK  (G2078) eschatos see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From  (G1519) eis; inside (as preposition or adjective) -- (with-)in(-ner, -to, -ward). see GREEK  (G1519) eis
From  (G2080) eso; from inside; also used as equivalent to  (G2080) eso (inside) -- inward(-ly), (from) within, without. see GREEK  (G2080) eso see GREEK  (G2080) eso
Comparative of  (G2080) eso; interior -- inner, within. see GREEK  (G2080) eso
From etes (a clansman); a comrade -- fellow, friend.
From  (G2087) heteros and  (G1100) glossa; other- tongued, i.e. A foreigner -- man of other tongue. see GREEK  (G2087) heteros see GREEK  (G1100) glossa
From  (G2087) heteros and  (G1320) didaskalos; to instruct differently -- teach other doctrine(-wise). see GREEK  (G2087) heteros see GREEK  (G1320) didaskalos

column7: to be yoked up differently, to be unequally yoked
column9: From a compound of  (G2087) heteros and  (G2218) zugos; to yoke up differently, i.e. (figuratively) to associate discordantly -- unequally yoke together with. see GREEK  (G2087) heteros see GREEK  (G2218) zugos
Of uncertain affinity; (an-, the) other or different -- altered, else, next (day), one, (an-)other, some, strange.
Adverb from  (G2087) heteros; differently -- otherwise. see GREEK  (G2087) heteros

Perhaps akin to  (G2094) etos; "yet," still (of time or degree) -- after that, also, ever, (any) further, (t-)henceforth (more), hereafter, (any) longer, (any) more(-one), now, still, yet. see GREEK  (G2094) etos
From  (G2092) hetoimos; to prepare -- prepare, provide, make ready. Compare  (G2680) kataskeuazo. see GREEK  (G2092) hetoimos see GREEK  (G2680) kataskeuazo
From  (G2090) hetoimazo; preparation -- preparation. see GREEK  (G2090) hetoimazo
From an old noun heteos (fitness); adjusted, i.e. Ready -- prepared, (made) ready(-iness, to our hand).
Adverb from  (G2092) hetoimos; in readiness -- ready. see GREEK  (G2092) hetoimos
Apparently a primary word; a year -- year.
Neuter of a primary eus (good); (adverbially) well -- good, well (done).
Of Hebrew origin ( (H2332) Chavvah); Eua (or Eva, i.e. Chavvah), the first woman -- Eve. see HEBREW  (H2332) Chavvah

column8: declare, bring good tidings, preach the gospel.
column9: From  (G2095) eu and  (G32) aggelos; to announce good news ("evangelize") especially the gospel -- declare, bring (declare, show) glad (good) tidings, preach (the gospel). see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G32) aggelos
From the same as  (G2097) euaggelizo; a good message, i.e. The gospel -- gospel. see GREEK  (G2097) euaggelizo

column7: an evangelist, a bringer of good news
column9: From  (G2097) euaggelizo; a preacher of the gospel -- evangelist. see GREEK  (G2097) euaggelizo
From  (G2101) euarestos; to gratify entirely -- please (well). see GREEK  (G2101) euarestos
From  (G2095) eu and  (G701) arestos; fully agreeable -- acceptable(-ted), wellpleasing. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G701) arestos
Adverb from  (G2101) euarestos; quite agreeably -- acceptably, + please well. see GREEK  (G2101) euarestos
From  (G2095) eu and  (G1014) boulomai; good-willer; Eubulus, a Christian -- Eubulus. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G1014) boulomai
From  (G2095) eu and  (G1096) ginomai; well born, i.e. (literally) high in rank, or (figuratively) generous -- more noble, nobleman. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
Feminine from  (G2095) eu and the alternate of  (G2203) Zeus (as the god of the weather); a clear sky, i.e. Fine weather -- fair weather. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G2203) Zeus

column7: to think well of, to be well-pleased
column8: think good, be well pleased, be willing.
column9: From  (G2095) eu and  (G1380) dokeo; to think well of, i.e. Approve (an act); specially, to approbate (a person or thing) -- think good, (be well) please(-d), be the good (have, take) pleasure, be willing. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G1380) dokeo

From a presumed compound of  (G2095) eu and the base of  (G1380) dokeo; satisfaction, i.e. (subjectively) delight, or (objectively) kindness, wish, purpose -- desire, good pleasure (will), X seem good. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G1380) dokeo
From  (G2110) euergetes; beneficence (genitive case or specially) -- benefit, good deed done. see GREEK  (G2110) euergetes
From  (G2110) euergetes; to be philanthropic -- do good. see GREEK  (G2110) euergetes

column7: a doer of good, a benefactor
column9: From  (G2095) eu and the base of  (G2041) ergon; a worker of good, i.e. (specially) a philanthropist -- benefactor. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G2041) ergon
From  (G2095) eu and a derivative of  (G5087) tithemi; well placed, i.e. (figuratively) appropriate -- fit, meet. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
Adverb from  (G2117) euthus; directly, i.e. At once or soon -- anon, as soon as, forthwith, immediately, shortly, straightway. see GREEK  (G2117) euthus

column8: run, sail with a straight course.
column9: From  (G2117) euthus and  (G1408) dromos; to lay a straight course, i.e. Sail direct -- (come) with a straight course. see GREEK  (G2117) euthus see GREEK  (G1408) dromos
From  (G2115) euthumos; to cheer up, i.e. (intransitively) be cheerful; neuter comparative (adverbially) more cheerfully -- be of good cheer (merry). see GREEK  (G2115) euthumos
From  (G2095) eu and  (G2372) thumos; in fine spirits, i.e. Cheerful -- of good cheer, the more cheerfully. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G2372) thumos
From  (G2117) euthus; to straighten (level); technically, to steer -- governor, make straight. see GREEK  (G2117) euthus

column8: by and by, forthwith, immediately, straightway.
column9: Perhaps from  (G2095) eu and  (G5087) tithemi; straight, i.e. (literally) level, or (figuratively) true; adverbially (of time) at once -- anon, by and by, forthwith, immediately, straightway. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From  (G2117) euthus; rectitude -- righteousness. see GREEK  (G2117) euthus
From  (G2121) eukairos; to have good time, i.e. Opportunity or leisure -- have leisure (convenient time), spend time. see GREEK  (G2121) eukairos
From  (G2121) eukairos; a favorable occasion -- opportunity. see GREEK  (G2121) eukairos
From  (G2095) eu and  (G2540) kairos; well-timed, i.e. Opportune -- convenient, in time of need. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G2540) kairos
Adverb from  (G2121) eukairos; opportunely -- conveniently, in season. see GREEK  (G2121) eukairos
Comparative of a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G2873) kopos; better for toil, i.e. More facile -- easier. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G2873) kopos
From  (G2126) eulabes; properly, caution, i.e. (religiously) reverence (piety); by implication, dread (concretely) -- fear(-ed). see GREEK  (G2126) eulabes
Middle voice from  (G2126) eulabes; to be circumspect, i.e. (by implication) to be apprehensive; religiously, to reverence -- (moved with) fear. see GREEK  (G2126) eulabes
From  (G2095) eu and  (G2983) lambano; taking well (carefully), i.e. Circumspect (religiously, pious) -- devout. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G2983) lambano

From a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G3056) logos; to speak well of, i.e. (religiously) to bless (thank or invoke a benediction upon, prosper) -- bless, praise. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3056) logos
From  (G2127) eulogeo; adorable -- blessed. see GREEK  (G2127) eulogeo

From the same as  (G2127) eulogeo; fine speaking, i.e. Elegance of language; commendation ("eulogy"), i.e. (reverentially) adoration; religiously, benediction; by implication, consecration; by extension, benefit or largess -- blessing (a matter of) bounty (X -tifully), fair speech. see GREEK  (G2127) eulogeo
From  (G2095) eu and a presumed derivative of  (G3330) metadidomi; good at imparting, i.e. Liberal -- ready to distribute. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3330) metadidomi

column7: victorious, Eunice, the mother of Timothy
column9: From  (G2095) eu and  (G3529) nike; victorious; Eunice, a Jewess -- Eunice. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3529) nike

column7: to think kindly of, to be favorable
column9: From a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G3563) nous; to be well- minded, i.e. Reconcile -- agree. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3563) nous
From the same as  (G2132) eunoeo; kindness; euphemistically, conjugal duty -- benevolence, good will. see GREEK  (G2132) eunoeo
From  (G2135) eunouchos; to castrate (figuratively, live unmarried) -- make...eunuch. see GREEK  (G2135) eunouchos

From eune (a bed) and  (G2192) echo; a castrated person (such being employed in Oriental bed-chambers); by extension an impotent or unmarried man; by implication, a chamberlain (state-officer) -- eunuch. see GREEK  (G2192) echo

column7: perhaps "success", Euodia, a Christian at Philippi
column9: From the same as  (G2137) euodoo; fine travelling; Euodia, a Christian woman -- Euodias. see GREEK  (G2137) euodoo

From a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G3598) hodos; to help on the road, i.e. (passively) succeed in reaching; figuratively, to succeed in business affairs -- (have a) prosper(-ous journey). see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3598) hodos
From  (G2095) eu and  (G3982) peitho; good for persuasion, i.e. (intransitively) complaint -- easy to be intreated. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3982) peitho

From  (G2095) eu and a derivative of a presumed compound of  (G4012) peri and  (G2476) histemi; well standing around, i.e. (a competitor) thwarting (a racer) in every direction (figuratively, of sin in genitive case) -- which doth so easily beset. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4012) peri see GREEK  (G2476) histemi
From a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G4160) poieo; well-doing, i.e. Beneficence -- to do good. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4160) poieo

From a compound of  (G2090) hetoimazo and the base of  (G4197) poreia; (intransitively) to be good for passing through, i.e. (figuratively) have pecuniary means -- ability. see GREEK  (G2090) hetoimazo see GREEK  (G4197) poreia
From the same as  (G2141) euporeo; pecuniary resources -- wealth. see GREEK  (G2141) euporeo
From a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G4241) prepo; good suitableness, i.e. Gracefulness -- grace. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4241) prepo
From  (G2095) eu and a derivative of  (G4327) prosdechomai; well-received, i.e. Approved, favorable -- acceptable(-ted). see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4327) prosdechomai

From  (G2095) eu and the same as  (G4332) prosedreuo; sitting well towards, i.e. (figuratively) assiduous (neuter, diligent service) -- X attend upon. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4332) prosedreuo

column7: to be of good countenance, to look well
column9: From a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G4383) prosopon; to be of good countenance, i.e. (figuratively) to make a display -- make a fair show. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4383) prosopon

A prolonged form of a primary heuro (hyoo'-ro), which (together with another cognate form) heureo (hyoo-reh'-o) is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find (literally or figuratively)
From Euros (the east wind) and  (G2830) kludon; a storm from the East (or southeast), i.e. (in modern phrase) a Levanter -- Euroklydon. see GREEK  (G2830) kludon
From eurus (wide) and  (G5561) chora; spacious -- broad. see GREEK  (G5561) chora
From  (G2152) eusebes; piety; specially, the gospel scheme -- godliness, holiness. see GREEK  (G2152) eusebes
From  (G2152) eusebes; to be pious, i.e. (towards God) to worship, or (towards parents) to respect (support) -- show piety, worship. see GREEK  (G2152) eusebes
From  (G2095) eu and  (G4576) sebomai; well-reverent, i.e. Pious -- devout, godly. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4576) sebomai
Adverb from  (G2152) eusebes; piously -- godly. see GREEK  (G2152) eusebes
From  (G2095) eu and the base of  (G4591) semaino; well indicated, i.e. (figuratively) significant -- easy to be understood. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4591) semaino
From  (G2095) eu and  (G4698) splagchnon; well compassioned, i.e. Sympathetic -- pitiful, tender-hearted. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4698) splagchnon
Adverb from  (G2158) euschemon; decorously -- decently, honestly. see GREEK  (G2158) euschemon
From  (G2158) euschemon; decorousness -- comeliness. see GREEK  (G2158) euschemon
From  (G2095) eu and  (G4976) schema; well-formed, i.e. (figuratively) decorous, noble (in rank) -- comely, honourable. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G4976) schema

Adverb from a compound of  (G2095) eu and a derivative of teino (to stretch); in a well-strung manner, i.e. (figuratively) intensely (in a good sense, cogently; in a bad one, fiercely) -- mightily, vehemently. see GREEK  (G2095) eu

From a compound of  (G2095) eu and a derivative of the base of  (G5157) trope (meaning well-turned, i.e. Ready at repartee, jocose); witticism, i.e. (in a vulgar sense) ribaldry -- jesting. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5157) trope

column7: well-fated, Eutychus, a young man restored to life by Paul
column9: From  (G2095) eu and a derivative of  (G5177) tugchano; well- fated, i.e. Fortunate; Eutychus, a young man -- Eutychus. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5177) tugchano
From  (G2163) euphemos; good language ("euphemy"), i.e. Praise (repute) -- good report. see GREEK  (G2163) euphemos
From  (G2095) eu and  (G5345) pheme; well spoken of, i.e. Reputable -- of good report. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5345) pheme

column7: to bear well, to be fruitful
column9: From  (G2095) eu and  (G5409) phoreo; to bear well, i.e. Be fertile -- bring forth abundantly. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5409) phoreo

From  (G2095) eu and  (G5424) phren; to put (middle voice or passively, be) in a good frame of mind, i.e. Rejoice -- fare, make glad, be (make) merry, rejoice. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5424) phren
Of foreign origin (compare  (H6578) Prath); Euphrates, a river of Asia -- Euphrates. see HEBREW  (H6578) Prath
From the same as  (G2165) euphraino; joyfulness -- gladness, joy. see GREEK  (G2165) euphraino
From  (G2170) eucharistos; to be grateful, i.e. (actively) to express gratitude (towards); specially, to say grace at a meal -- (give) thank(-ful, -s). see GREEK  (G2170) eucharistos
From  (G2170) eucharistos; gratitude; actively, grateful language (to God, as an act of worship) -- thankfulness, (giving of) thanks(-giving). see GREEK  (G2170) eucharistos
From  (G2095) eu and a derivative of  (G5483) charizomai; well favored, i.e. (by implication) grateful -- thankful. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5483) charizomai
From  (G2172) euchomai; properly, a wish, expressed as a petition to God, or in votive obligation -- prayer, vow. see GREEK  (G2172) euchomai
Middle voice of a primary verb; to wish; by implication, to pray to God -- pray, will, wish.
From  (G2095) eu and  (G5543) chrestos; easily used, i.e. Useful -- profitable, meet for use. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5543) chrestos

column8: be of good comfort, have courage
column9: From a compound of  (G2095) eu and  (G5590) psuche; to be in good spirits, i.e. Feel encouraged -- be of good comfort. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G5590) psuche
From a compound of  (G2095) eu and a derivative of  (G3605) ozo; good-scentedness, i.e. Fragrance -- sweet savour (smell, -smelling). see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3605) ozo

From  (G2095) eu and  (G3686) onoma; properly, well-named (good-omened), i.e. The left (which was the lucky side among the pagan Greeks); neuter as adverbial, at the left hand -- (on the) left. see GREEK  (G2095) eu see GREEK  (G3686) onoma
From  (G1909) epi and  (G242) hallomai; to spring upon -- leap on. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G242) hallomai
From  (G1909) epi and  (G530) hapax; upon one occasion (only) -- (at) once (for all). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G530) hapax
From  (G2181) Ephesos; Ephesine, or situated at Ephesus -- of Ephesus. see GREEK  (G2181) Ephesos
From  (G2181) Ephesos; an Ephesian or inhabitant of Ephesus -- Ephesian, of Ephesus. see GREEK  (G2181) Ephesos

column7: Ephesus, a city in Asia Minor
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Ephesus, a city of Asia Minor -- Ephesus.
From a compound of  (G1909) epi and  (G2147) heurisko; a discoverer, i.e. Contriver -- inventor. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2147) heurisko

column7: a class (of priests detailed for service in the temple)
column9: From  (G2184) ephemeros; diurnality, i.e. (specially) the quotidian rotation or class of the Jewish priests' service at the Temple, as distributed by families -- course. see GREEK  (G2184) ephemeros
From  (G1909) epi and  (G2250) hemera; for a day ("ephemeral"), i.e. Diurnal -- daily. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2250) hemera
From  (G1909) epi and a cognate of  (G2240) heko; to arrive upon, i.e. Extend to -- reach. see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2240) heko

column7: to set upon, set up, to stand upon, be present
column8: assault, come unto, be at hand, stand over.
column9: From  (G1909) epi and  (G2476) histemi; to stand upon, i.e. Be present (in various applications, friendly or otherwise, usually literal); --assault, come (in, to, unto, upon), be at hand (instant), present, stand (before, by, over). see GREEK  (G1909) epi see GREEK  (G2476) histemi
Of Hebrew origin ( (H669) 'Ephrayim or better  (H6085) Ephrown); Ephraim, a place in Palestine -- Ephraim. see HEBREW  (H669) 'Ephrayim see HEBREW  (H6085) Ephrown
Of Chaldee origin ( (H6606) pthach); be opened! -- Ephphatha. see HEBREW  (H6606) pthach
Feminine of  (G2190) echthros; hostility; by implication, a reason for opposition -- enmity, hatred. see GREEK  (G2190) echthros
From a primary echtho (to hate); hateful (passively, odious, or actively, hostile); usually as a noun, an adversary (especially Satan) -- enemy, foe.
Of uncertain origin; an adder or other poisonous snake (literally or figuratively) -- viper.

Including an alternate form scheo skheh'-o; (used in certain tenses only); a primary verb; to hold (used in very various applications, literally or figuratively, direct or remote; such as possession; ability, contiuity, relation, or condition) -- be (able, X hold, possessed with), accompany, + begin to amend, can(+ -not), X conceive, count, diseased, do + eat, + enjoy, + fear, following, have, hold, keep, + lack, + go to law, lie, + must needs, + of necessity, + need, next, + recover, + reign, + rest, + return, X sick, take for, + tremble, + uncircumcised, use.

column8: even, as far as, how long, until, while.
column9: Of uncertain affinity; a conjunction, preposition and adverb of continuance, until (of time and place) -- even (until, unto), (as) far (as), how long, (un-)til(-l), (hither-, un-, up) to, while(-s).

column7: Zebulun, a son of Jacob and one of the Israelite tribes
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H2074) Zbuwluwn); Zabulon (i.e. Zebulon), a region of Palestine -- Zabulon. see HEBREW  (H2074) Zbuwluwn
Of Hebrew origin (compare  (H2140) Zakkay); Zacchaeus, an Israelite -- Zacchaeus. see HEBREW  (H2140) Zakkay
Of Hebrew origin ( (H2226) Zerach); Zara, (i.e. Zerach), an Israelite -- Zara. see HEBREW  (H2226) Zerach

column7: Zacharias, the father of John the Baptist, Zechariah, the son of Barachiah
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H2148) Zkaryah); Zacharias (i.e. Zechariah), the name of two Israelites -- Zacharias. see HEBREW  (H2148) Zkaryah
A primary verb; to live (literally or figuratively) -- life(-time), (a-)live(-ly), quick.

column7: Zebedee, the father of the apostles James and John
column9: Of Hebrew origin (compare  (H2067) Zabdiy); Zebedaeus, an Israelite -- Zebedee. see HEBREW  (H2067) Zabdiy
From  (G2204) zeo; boiled, i.e. (by implication) calid (figuratively, fervent) -- hot. see GREEK  (G2204) zeo
From the same as  (G2218) zugos; a couple, i.e. A team (of oxen yoked together) or brace (of birds tied together) -- yoke, pair. see GREEK  (G2218) zugos
Feminine of a derivative (at the second stage) from the same as  (G2218) zugos; a fastening (tiller-rope) -- band. see GREEK  (G2218) zugos

column7: Zeus, the greatest of the pagan Gk. gods
column9: Of uncertain affinity; in the oblique cases there is used instead of it a (probably cognate) name; Dis (deece), which is otherwise obsolete; Zeus or Dis (among the Latins, Jupiter or Jove), the supreme deity of the Greeks -- Jupiter.
A primary verb; to be hot (boil, of liquids; or glow, of solids), i.e. (figuratively) be fervid (earnest) -- be fervent.

column7: to have warmth of feeling for or against, to be zealous or jealous
column9: From  (G2204) zeo; properly, heat, i.e. (figuratively) "zeal" (in a favorable sense, ardor; in an unfavorable one, jealousy, as of a husband (figuratively, of God), or an enemy, malice) -- emulation, envy(-ing), fervent mind, indignation, jealousy, zeal. see GREEK  (G2204) zeo
From  (G2205) zelos; to have warmth of feeling for or against -- affect, covet (earnestly), (have) desire, (move with) envy, be jealous over, (be) zealous(-ly affect). see GREEK  (G2205) zelos
From  (G2206) zeloo; a "zealot" -- zealous. see GREEK  (G2206) zeloo

column7: the Zealot, a member of a Jewish political party
column9: The same as  (G2208) Zelotes; a Zealot, i.e. (specially) partisan for Jewish political independence -- Zelotes. see GREEK  (G2208) Zelotes
Probably akin to the base of  (G1150) damazo (through the idea of violence); detriment -- damage, loss. see GREEK  (G1150) damazo
From  (G2209) zemia; to injure, i.e. (reflexively or passively) to experience detriment -- be cast away, receive damage, lose, suffer loss. see GREEK  (G2209) zemia
Probably contracted from a poetic form of  (G2203) Zeus and  (G1435) doron; Jove-given; Zenas, a Christian -- Zenas. see GREEK  (G2203) Zeus see GREEK  (G1435) doron

Of uncertain affinity; to seek (literally or figuratively); specially, (by Hebraism) to worship (God), or (in a bad sense) to plot (against life) -- be (go) about, desire, endeavour, enquire (for), require, (X will) seek (after, for, means). Compare  (G4441) punthanomai. see GREEK  (G4441) punthanomai
From  (G2212) zeteo; a search (properly concretely), i.e. (in words) a debate -- question. see GREEK  (G2212) zeteo
From  (G2212) zeteo; a searching (properly, the act), i.e. A dispute or its theme -- question. see GREEK  (G2212) zeteo

column7: zizanium (a kind of darnel resembling wheat)
column9: Of uncertain origin; darnel or false grain -- tares.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H2216) Zrubbabel); Zorobabel (i.e. Zerubbabel), an Israelite -- Zorobabel. see HEBREW  (H2216) Zrubbabel
Akin to the base of  (G3509) nephos; gloom (as shrouding like a cloud) -- blackness, darkness, mist. see GREEK  (G3509) nephos

From the root of zeugnumi (to join, especially by a "yoke"); a coupling, i.e. (figuratively) servitude (a law or obligation); also (literally) the beam of the balance (as connecting the scales) -- pair of balances, yoke.
Probably from  (G2204) zeo; ferment (as if boiling up) -- leaven. see GREEK  (G2204) zeo
From  (G2219) zume; to cause to ferment -- leaven. see GREEK  (G2219) zume

From the same as  (G2226) zoon and  (G64) agreuo; to take alive (make a prisoner of war), i.e. (figuratively) to capture or ensnare -- take captive, catch. see GREEK  (G2226) zoon see GREEK  (G64) agreuo
From  (G2198) zao; life (literally or figuratively) -- life(-time). Compare  (G5590) psuche. see GREEK  (G2198) zao see GREEK  (G5590) psuche
Probably akin to the base of  (G2218) zugos; a belt; by implication, a pocket -- girdle, purse. see GREEK  (G2218) zugos
From  (G2223) zone; to bind about (especially with a belt) -- gird. see GREEK  (G2223) zone

From the same as  (G2226) zoon and a derivative of  (G1096) ginomai; to engender alive, i.e. (by analogy) to rescue (passively, be saved) from death -- live, preserve. see GREEK  (G2226) zoon see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
Neuter of a derivative of  (G2198) zao; a live thing, i.e. An animal -- beast. see GREEK  (G2198) zao
From the same as  (G2226) zoon and  (G4160) poieo; to (re-)vitalize (literally or figuratively) -- make alive, give life, quicken. see GREEK  (G2226) zoon see GREEK  (G4160) poieo

A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than -- and, but (either), (n-)either, except it be, (n-)or (else), rather, save, than, that, what, yea. Often used in connection with other particles. Compare especially  (G2235) ede,  (G2260) eper,  (G2273) etoi. see GREEK  (G2235) ede see GREEK  (G2260) eper see GREEK  (G2273) etoi
An adverb of confirmation; perhaps intensive of  (G2228) e; used only (in the New Testament) before  (G3303) men; assuredly -- surely. see GREEK  (G2228) e see GREEK  (G3303) men
From  (G2232) hegemon; to act as ruler -- be governor. see GREEK  (G2232) hegemon
From  (G2232) hegemon; government, i.e. (in time) official term -- reign. see GREEK  (G2232) hegemon
From  (G2233) hegeomai; a leader, i.e. Chief person (or figuratively, place) of a province -- governor, prince, ruler. see GREEK  (G2233) hegeomai

Middle voice of a (presumed) strengthened form of  (G71) ago; to lead, i.e. Command (with official authority); figuratively, to deem, i.e. Consider -- account, (be) chief, count, esteem, governor, judge, have the rule over, suppose, think. see GREEK  (G71) ago
Adverb from a derivative of the base of  (G2237) hedone; sweetly, i.e. (figuratively) with pleasure -- gladly. see GREEK  (G2237) hedone

column8: already, even now, by this time.
column9: Apparently from  (G2228) e (or possibly  (G2229) e) and  (G1211) de; even now -- already, (even) now (already), by this time. see GREEK  (G2228) e see GREEK  (G2229) e see GREEK  (G1211) de
Neuter plural of the superlative of the same as  (G2234) hedeos; with great pleasure -- most (very) gladly. see GREEK  (G2234) hedeos
From handano (to please); sensual delight; by implication, desire -- lust, pleasure.
Neuter of the compound of the same as  (G2234) hedeos and  (G3744) osme; a sweet-scented plant, i.e. Mint -- mint. see GREEK  (G2234) hedeos see GREEK  (G3744) osme
A strengthened form of  (G1485) ethos; usage, i.e. (plural) moral habits -- manners. see GREEK  (G1485) ethos
A primary verb; to arrive, i.e. Be present (literally or figuratively) -- come.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H410) 'el with pronominal suffix); my God -- Eli. see HEBREW  (H410) 'el
Of Hebrew origin ( (H5941) Eliy); Heli (i.e. Eli), an Israelite -- Heli. see HEBREW  (H5941) Eliy
Of Hebrew origin ( (H452) 'Eliyah); Helias (i.e. Elijah), an Israelite -- Elias. see HEBREW  (H452) 'Eliyah
From the same as  (G2245) helikos; maturity (in years or size) -- age, stature. see GREEK  (G2245) helikos
From helix (a comrade, i.e. One of the same age); as big as, i.e. (interjectively) how much -- how (what) great.
From hele (a ray; perhaps akin to the alternate of  (G138) haireomai); the sun; by implication, light -- + east, sun. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
Of uncertain affinity; a stud, i.e. Spike -- nail.
Accusative case plural of  (G1473) ego; us -- our, us, we. see GREEK  (G1473) ego
Nominative plural of  (G1473) ego; we (only used when emphatic) -- us, we (ourselves). see GREEK  (G1473) ego

Feminine (with  (G5610) hora implied) of a derivative of hemai (to sit; akin to the base of  (G1476) hedraios) meaning tame, i.e. Gentle; day, i.e. (literally) the time space between dawn and dark, or the whole  (G24) aganaktesis hours (but several days were usually reckoned by the Jews as inclusive of the parts of both extremes); figuratively, a period (always defined more or less clearly by the context) -- age, + alway, (mid-)day (by day, (-ly)), + for ever, judgment, (day) time, while, years. see GREEK  (G5610) hora see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios
From  (G2349) thnetos; our -- our, your (by a different reading). see GREEK  (G2349) thnetos
A prolonged form of  (G2358) thriambeuo; I was -- be, was. (Sometimes unexpressed). see GREEK  (G2358) thriambeuo
From a presumed compound of the base of  (G2255) hemisu and  (G2348) thnesko; half dead, i.e. Entirely exhausted -- half dead. see GREEK  (G2255) hemisu see GREEK  (G2348) thnesko
Dative case plural of  (G1473) ego; to (or for, with, by) us -- our, (for) us, we. see GREEK  (G1473) ego
Neuter of a derivative from an inseparable prefix akin to  (G260) hama (through the idea of partition involved in connection) and meaning semi-; (as noun) half -- half. see GREEK  (G260) hama
From the base of  (G2255) hemisu and  (G5610) hora; a half-hour -- half an hour. see GREEK  (G2255) hemisu see GREEK  (G5610) hora
Genitive case plural of  (G1473) ego; of (or from) us -- our (company), us, we. see GREEK  (G1473) ego

column7: agree, be, have charge of, hold, use
column8: agree, be, have charge of, hold, use.
column9: Imperfect of  (G1510) eimi; I (thou, etc.) Was (wast or were) -- + agree, be, X have (+ charge of), hold, use, was(-t), were. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
Of uncertain affinity; at which time -- when.
From  (G2228) e and  (G4007) per; than at all (or than perhaps, than indeed) -- than. see GREEK  (G2228) e see GREEK  (G4007) per
Probably from  (G2031) epos; properly, affable, i.e. Mild or kind -- gentle. see GREEK  (G2031) epos
Of Hebrew origin ( (H6147) Er); Er, an Israelite -- Er. see HEBREW  (H6147) Er
Perhaps by transposition from  (G2048) eremos (through the idea of stillness); tranquil -- quiet. see GREEK  (G2048) eremos

column7: perhaps "son of a hero", Herod, the name of several kings of the Jews
column9: Compound of heros (a "hero") and  (G1491) eidos; heroic; Herod, the name of four Jewish kings -- Herod. see GREEK  (G1491) eidos
Plural of a derivative of  (G2264) Herodes; Herodians, i.e. Partisans of Herod -- Herodians. see GREEK  (G2264) Herodes

column7: Herodias, granddaughter of Herod the Great
column9: From  (G2264) Herodes; Herodias, a woman of the Heodian family -- Herodias. see GREEK  (G2264) Herodes
From  (G2264) Herodes; Herodion, a Christian -- Herodion. see GREEK  (G2264) Herodes
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3470) Ysha'yah); Hesaias (i.e. Jeshajah), an Israelite -- Esaias. see HEBREW  (H3470) Ysha'yah
Of Hebrew origin ( (H6215) Esav); Esau, an Edomite -- Esau. see HEBREW  (H6215) Esav

column8: cease, hold peace, be quiet, rest.
column9: From the same as  (G2272) hesuchios; to keep still (intransitively), i.e. Refrain from labor, meddlesomeness or speech -- cease, hold peace, be quiet, rest. see GREEK  (G2272) hesuchios
Feminine of  (G2272) hesuchios; (as noun) stillness, i.e. Desistance from bustle or language -- quietness, silence. see GREEK  (G2272) hesuchios

A prolonged form of a compound probably of a derivative of the base of  (G1476) hedraios and perhaps  (G2192) echo; properly, keeping one's seat (sedentary), i.e. (by implication) still (undisturbed, undisturbing) -- peaceable, quiet. see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From  (G2228) e and  (G5104) toi; either indeed -- whether. see GREEK  (G2228) e see GREEK  (G5104) toi
From the same as  (G2276) hetton; to make worse, i.e. Vanquish (literally or figuratively); by implication, to rate lower -- be inferior, overcome. see GREEK  (G2276) hetton
From  (G2274) hettao; a deterioration, i.e. (objectively) failure or (subjectively) loss -- diminishing, fault. see GREEK  (G2274) hettao
Neuter of comparative of heka (slightly) used for that of  (G2556) kakos; worse (as noun); by implication, less (as adverb) -- less, worse. see GREEK  (G2556) kakos
Third person singular imperative of  (G1510) eimi; let him (or it) be -- let... Be. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column7: to make a loud noise, to sound
column9: From  (G2279) echos; to make a loud noise, i.e. Reverberate -- roar, sound. see GREEK  (G2279) echos
Of uncertain affinity; a loud or confused noise ("echo"), i.e. Roar; figuratively, a rumor -- fame, sound.
Of uncertain origin; Thaddaeus, one of the Apostles -- Thaddaeus.
Probably prolonged from  (G251) hals; the sea (genitive case or specially) -- sea. see GREEK  (G251) hals
Probably akin to thallo (to warm); to brood, i.e. (figuratively) to foster -- cherish.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H8559) Tamar); Thamar (i.e. Tamar), an Israelitess -- Thamar. see HEBREW  (H8559) Tamar
From  (G2285) thambos; to stupefy (with surprise), i.e. Astound -- amaze, astonish. see GREEK  (G2285) thambos
Akin to an obsolete tapho (to dumbfound); stupefaction (by surprise), i.e. Astonishment -- X amazed, + astonished, wonder.
From  (G2288) thanatos; fatal, i.e. Poisonous -- deadly. see GREEK  (G2288) thanatos
From (the feminine form of)  (G2288) thanatos and  (G5342) phero; death-bearing, i.e. Fatal -- deadly. see GREEK  (G2288) thanatos see GREEK  (G5342) phero
From  (G2348) thnesko; (properly, an adjective used as a noun) death (literally or figuratively) -- X deadly, (be...) Death. see GREEK  (G2348) thnesko

column8: become dead, put to death, kill, mortify.
column9: From  (G2288) thanatos to kill (literally or figuratively) -- become dead, (cause to be) put to death, kill, mortify. see GREEK  (G2288) thanatos
A primary verb; to celebrate funeral rites, i.e. Inter -- bury.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H8646) Terach); Thara (i.e. Terach), the father of Abraham -- Thara. see HEBREW  (H8646) Terach

column8: be bold, have confidence, be confident.
column9: Another form for  (G2293) tharseo; to exercise courage -- be bold, X boldly, have confidence, be confident. Compare  (G5111) tolmao. see GREEK  (G2293) tharseo see GREEK  (G5111) tolmao
From  (G2294) tharsos; to have courage -- be of good cheer (comfort). Compare  (G2292) tharrheo. see GREEK  (G2294) tharsos see GREEK  (G2292) tharrheo
Akin (by transposition) to thrasos (daring); boldness (subjectively) -- courage.
Apparently from a form of  (G2300) theaomai; wonder (properly concrete; but by implication, abstract) -- admiration. see GREEK  (G2300) theaomai
From  (G2295) thauma; to wonder; by implication, to admire -- admire, have in admiration, marvel, wonder. see GREEK  (G2295) thauma
From  (G2295) thauma; wondrous, i.e. (neuter as noun) a miracle -- wonderful thing. see GREEK  (G2295) thauma
From  (G2296) thaumazo; wondered at, i.e. (by implication) wonderful -- marvel(-lous). see GREEK  (G2296) thaumazo
Feminine of  (G2316) theos; a female deity -- goddess. see GREEK  (G2316) theos

A prolonged form of a primary verb; to look closely at, i.e. (by implication) perceive (literally or figuratively); by extension to visit -- behold, look (upon), see. Compare  (G3700) optanomai. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai

column8: to put to shame, expose publicly
column9: From  (G2302) theatron; to expose as a spectacle -- make a gazing stock. see GREEK  (G2302) theatron
From  (G2300) theaomai; a place for public show ("theatre"), i.e. General audience-room; by implication, a show itself (figuratively) -- spectacle, theatre. see GREEK  (G2300) theaomai
Probably neuter of  (G2304) theios (in its original sense of flashing); sulphur -- brimstone. see GREEK  (G2304) theios
From  (G2316) theos; godlike (neuter as noun, divinity): - divine, godhead. see GREEK  (G2316) theos
From  (G2304) theios; divinity (abstractly) -- godhead. see GREEK  (G2304) theios
From  (G2303) theion and  (G1491) eidos; sulphur-like, i.e. Sulphurous -- brimstone. see GREEK  (G2303) theion

From the prolonged form of  (G2309) ethelo; a determination (properly, the thing), i.e. (actively) choice (specially, purpose, decree; abstractly, volition) or (passively) inclination -- desire, pleasure, will. see GREEK  (G2309) ethelo
From  (G2309) ethelo; determination (properly, the act), i.e. Option -- will. see GREEK  (G2309) ethelo

Thel'-o or thel'-o or in certain tenses theleo thel-eh'-o, and etheleo eth-el-eh'-o, which are otherwise obsolete; apparently strengthened from the alternate form of  (G138) haireomai; to determine (as an active option from subjective impulse; whereas  (G1014) boulomai properly denotes rather a passive acquiescence in objective considerations), i.e. Choose or prefer (literally or figuratively); by implication, to wish, i.e. Be inclined to (sometimes adverbially, gladly); impersonally for the future tense, to be about to; by Hebraism, to delight in -- desire, be disposed (forward), intend, list, love, mean, please, have rather, (be) will (have, -ling, - ling(-ly)). see GREEK  (G138) haireomai see GREEK  (G1014) boulomai
From a derivative of  (G5087) tithemi; something put down, i.e. A substruction (of a building, etc.), (literally or figuratively) -- foundation. see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From  (G2310) themelios; to lay a basis for, i.e. (literally) erect, or (figuratively) consolidate -- (lay the) found(- ation), ground, settle. see GREEK  (G2310) themelios
From  (G2316) theos and  (G1321) didasko; divinely instructed -- taught of God. see GREEK  (G2316) theos see GREEK  (G1321) didasko
From  (G2314) theomachos; to resist deity -- fight against God. see GREEK  (G2314) theomachos
From  (G2316) theos and  (G3164) machomai; an opponent of deity -- to fight against God. see GREEK  (G2316) theos see GREEK  (G3164) machomai
From  (G2316) theos and a presumed derivative of  (G4154) pneo; divinely breathed in -- given by inspiration of God. see GREEK  (G2316) theos see GREEK  (G4154) pneo
Of uncertain affinity; a deity, especially (with  (G3588) ho) the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very -- X exceeding, God, god(-ly, -ward). see GREEK  (G3588) ho
From  (G2318) theosebes; devoutness, i.e. Piety -- godliness. see GREEK  (G2318) theosebes
From  (G2316) theos and  (G4576) sebomai; reverent of God, i.e. Pious -- worshipper of God. see GREEK  (G2316) theos see GREEK  (G4576) sebomai
From  (G2316) theos and the base of  (G4767) stugnetos; hateful to God, i.e. Impious -- hater of God. see GREEK  (G2316) theos see GREEK  (G4767) stugnetos
From  (G2316) theos; divinity (abstractly) -- godhead. see GREEK  (G2316) theos

column7: friend of God, Theophilus, the addressee of Luke and Acts
column9: From  (G2316) theos and  (G5384) philos; friend of God; Theophilus, a Christian -- Theophilus. see GREEK  (G2316) theos see GREEK  (G5384) philos
From  (G2323) therapeuo; attendance (specially, medical, i.e. Cure); figuratively and collectively, domestics -- healing, household. see GREEK  (G2323) therapeuo
From the same as  (G2324) therapon; to wait upon menially, i.e. (figuratively) to adore (God), or (specially) to relieve (of disease) -- cure, heal, worship. see GREEK  (G2324) therapon
Apparently a participle from an otherwise obsolete derivative of the base of  (G2330) theros; a menial attendant (as if cherishing) -- servant. see GREEK  (G2330) theros
From  (G2330) theros (in the sense of the crop); to harvest -- reap. see GREEK  (G2330) theros
From  (G2325) therizo; reaping, i.e. The crop -- harvest. see GREEK  (G2325) therizo
From  (G2325) therizo; a harvester -- reaper. see GREEK  (G2325) therizo
From  (G2329) therme; to heat (oneself) -- (be) warm(-ed, self). see GREEK  (G2329) therme
From the base of  (G2330) theros; warmth -- heat. see GREEK  (G2330) theros
